Commentary: Hasan Ali starts with a length delivery, around leg, shaping away. Oshada Fernando leaves it alone. The keeper dives to his left to make a brilliant stop. The wind is coming into play already.
Well watched! Good length, outside off. Oshada Fernando leaves it alone for the keeper.

Hasan Ali asking the right questions here. It is a length ball that lands on middle and nips in a touch. Oshada Fernando stays inside the crease, tries to flick but plays all around it. He gets rapped on his pads. Ali appeals for lbw but the umpire shows no interest. The visitors decide to go against the review.
On a good length, outside off, shaping away with some bounce. Oshada Fernando watches it sail past him.
Length ball, on the pads. Fernando blocks it out.
A maiden to start the morning session on Day 1! This is bit fuller, on off. Fernando drives it back to the bowler who collects it on a bounce. A neat start for Pakistan.
Naseem Shah dishes a full-length delivery, outside off, angling across. Dimuth Karunaratne shoulders his arms at it.
Keeps it full yet again, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it alone for the keeper.
This one keeps low! It is interesting as it's just Day 1. On a length, angled across the left-hander, outside off. This one does not carry. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to poke but decides against it.
Outside off, left alone.
Five dots in a row! Full length, moving away, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne has no shot to offer.
Naseem Shah starts with a maiden as well! This time though he makes the batsman play. It is full and on off. Dimuth Karunaratne closes the face of the blade and blocks it towards mid on.
Length ball, angled into the pads. Oshada Fernando tucks it to mid-wicket.
Swing and a miss! Slightly short, outside off, this shapes away off the deck. Oshada Fernando stays on the back foot and tries to cut it away. He misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
This time he picks up the length quickly. Good length, wide outside off. Fernando leaves it alone.
Quick single! Oshada Fernando and Sri Lanka are off the mark. A length delivery, angled into the pads. Fernando blocks it to mid-wicket off the inner half. They cross for a single.
Length ball, on top of off. Dimuth Karunaratne defends it watchfully.
Full length, down leg. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to flick but fails to get any blade on it.
Shah serves it full and on off. Oshada Fernando works it to covers with an angled bat.
LEG BYE! A length ball, on the pads, Fernando fails to tickle it away. It goes to fine leg off his pads, They cross for a leg bye.
Goes full this time, on off. Dimuth Karunaratne gets on the front foot and pushes it to covers off the toe-end.
Two dots in a row now! Full length, angled across, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne gets behind the line and nudges it to the leg side.
Full length, on leg stump. Dimuth Karunaratne stays back and blocks it out solidly.

Four dots on the trot to end the over! It is on a full-length, on fifth stump, angled across. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to defend it out but decides against it. He has been very poor with his shot selection until now.
Outside off, left alone.
First positive stroke of the morning. Length ball, on the pads, Oshada Fernando flicks it to deep square leg and collects three runs.
Full length, on the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it to deep square leg for two runs.
Ali serves it on a length, around middle and leg. Dimuth Karunaratne tucks it to mid-wicket for a single now. 6 runs off the over already.
Back of a length, outside off. Oshada Fernando moves across and leaves it alone with a 360 spin inside the crease.
FOUR! Well played! It is full, wide outside off. Oshada Fernando gets on the front foot drives it through the gap at covers at finds the boundary. 10 runs off the over then.
Length ball, on off, flicked to the leg side.
Good length, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne shoulders his arms at it.
Third dot of the over! Shah stems in from over the wicket and hits the length hard, outside off and makes it shape in a touch. Dimuth Karunaratne has no shot to offer.
Shah serves it full, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne gets on the front foot and drives it to the right of extra cover. He fails to find the gap.
Back of a length, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to cut it away on the back foot and misses. He was not certain at all. Dimuth Karunaratne needs to keep his cool here.
NO BALL! It is well outside off, on a length. Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it alone. It could've been a third maiden for Shah but he has overstepped this time. The umpire signals a late no ball.
Full length, angled into the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne stays back and nudges it to fine leg. They cross for a single.
Hasan Ali sprays it down the leg side from over the wicket. Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it alone. Mohammad Rizwan collects it with a good dive to his right.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Dimuth Karunaratne. This is full, angled into the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne wrists it through square leg and bags a boundary. His first one of the innings.
NO BALL! Hasan Ali oversteps this time and has to reload here.
Length ball, on off, blocked out.
Full length, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it to mid-wicket.
Dimuth Karunaratne flicks this full delivery down to fine leg and collects a single.
Little bit of shape. On a length, outside off. Oshada Fernando shuffles across but leaves it alone.
This one is down the off side and Dimuth Karunaratne lets it through.
A sharp bouncer now, on off. Dimuth Karunaratne ducks under it.
Good length, on fourth stump, angled across. Dimuth Karunaratne gets on the front foot and punches it to extra cover.
Full length, on the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it to the leg side.
Short ball, wide outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne cuts it to covers off his back foot but with no timing.
Third maiden for Shah in this innings. It is a short one, on off. Dimuth Karunaratne ducks under it.
Starts off with a floater, full and on off. Oshada Fernando strokes it away towards mid on.
This is drifted in on a length and onto middle and leg. Fernando just nudges it onto the leg side.
Nice bit of flight on this occasion. This is angled in on middle, Fernando pushes it back towards the bowler.
On off, defended to the right of the bowler.
Floated and full, on off. Fernando eases it back to the bowler.
FOUR LEG BYES! It is tossed up, down leg. Fernando misses his flick. It takes his pads and races away down to fine leg boundary.
Shah serves a length delivery, on fourth stump, angled across. Left alone.
Full length, around middle. Dimuth Karunaratne steps down and drives it to mid on.
Length ball, on the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full length, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne drives it to the right of mid off. He gets across for a quick single.
Length ball, outside off. Fernando defends it to cover on the front foot. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Length ball, on off. Fernando gets behind the line and blocks it back to the bowler.
Shah serves it full, on off. Fernando drives it to mid on but not past the fielder.
Nauman Ali starts with a tossed up delivery on off, angling in, Dimuth Karunaratne knocks it to mid off.
Floated full and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne eases it towards long on for a single.
SIX! Good shot! This is slower through the air and on middle and off, Oshada Fernando dances down the track and just chips it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Tossed up on middle, Oshada Fernando blocks it down the pitch.
On middle, Oshada Fernando defends it to the off side.
Two to end the over. This is a bit short and on leg, Oshada Fernando pulls it away towards fine leg for a brace. 8 runs off the over then.
Slower ball from Ali. This is full and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Goes full again but down the leg, Oshada Fernando misses his flick and the ball goes straight to the keeper.
Good length on middle, angling in, Oshada Fernando blocks it back to the bowler.
Fullish delivery on leg, Oshada Fernando nudges it to the on side towards the square leg fielder.
On a length and around off, Oshada Fernando is solid in his defense here.
Length again and angling onto middle, Fernando pushes it back to the bowler.
Nicely looped up on middle, Karunaratne knocks it to the left of the bowler.
Tossed up full, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
A bit short on middle, Oshada Fernando defends it of his back foot. It is called a no ball for overstepping.
On middle, blocked out.
On a length and around middle, Oshada Fernando blocks it out.
Slower through the air and Ali pulls back the length as well. The ball turns away from the off pole as Fernando watchfully keeps it out on the off side.
Good length on middle and leg, Dimuth Karunaratne works it through square leg for one.
Pulls his length back a bit outside off, Oshada Fernando gets on top of it and punches it through covers for a brace.
On a length and outside off again, Oshada Fernando lifts his bat and leaves it alone.
This one keeps low. Hasan Ali bowls it full and way outside off, shaping away a bit, Oshada Fernando slashes his bat at it but misses it completely as it kept low.
Length ball on middle, Oshada Fernando nudges it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! This is a bit too full and outside off, Oshada Fernando loves width and plays a handsome drive through covers and picks up a boundary.
Tossed up full, angling down the leg, Dimuth Karunaratne misses his flick. It is called a no ball for overstepping. This is very poor from Ali.

Floated on middle and leg, angling down the leg, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards fine leg and picks up three runs. Fawad Alam from short fine leg chases it down and does well to pull the ball back in time, saves a run for his side.
BEATEN! This is slower through the air on off, turning away sharply. Oshada Fernando leans on to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tossed up on off, Oshada Fernando guides it to point with the outer half of his willow.
Shortish and on middle, Oshada Fernando blocks it down the pitch of his back foot.

FOUR! Nice shot! This is tossed up on middle, angling in, Oshada Fernando uses his feet and gets to the pitch of the ball and lofts it over the mid on fielder for a boundary. That brings up the 50 for Sri Lanka. This partnership is looking good now.
Floated on middle and leg, Oshada Fernando nudges it to mid-wicket.

Starts off from around the wicket and drifts it full and onto the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne works it 'round the corner for a single. What is happening out there? Yet another no ball by a spinner and this is just poor from Pakistan.
Flatter trajectory and around off, this is just eased through mid on for a single.
Pushed through on middle, Karunaratne drives it down to long on and rotates the strike.
Floats it up now, around the filfth stump line. Oshada Fernando watches it all the way through and leaves it alone.

A huge appeal for caught behind, but it is turned down! This is very well bowled, slightly tossed up, on a nagging length and closer to the off pole. Oshada Fernando presses forward to defend but gets beaten past the outside edge. The bowler is certain that there's an edge but there's not much enthusiasm from elsewhere.
Turning into middle and leg, nudged away onto the leg side.
Nicely flighted, around off. Fernando drives it towards extra cover.
Starts off with a full delivery on leg stump, Karunaratne eases it down to long on and collects a run.
Tossed up, on off, Fernando blocks it out.
FOUR! Beautifully played. This is tossed up on middle, Oshada Fernando uses his wrists to maneuver the ball past wide mid on and picks up a boundary. Brings up 1000 Test runs for himself as well.
Drifted onto middle and leg, Fernando keeps it out.
Floated up around middle, Oshada Fernando uses his feet and pushes it towards mid on and sets off for a quick single.
Switches to around the wicket for the left-hander and angles it into the pads, Karunaratne works it towards mid-wicket.
This is very full and on middle, Fernando flicks it away through mid-wicket and collects a single.
FOUR! Easily done! A half-volley on the pads and Dimuth Karunaratne just works it well in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Drifted onto off and just turning away a bit, Karunaratne deliberately opens the face of the bat and edges it down to third man for a run.
Around middle, flicked away to mid-wicket.

Nicely bowled! Slower through the air and tossed up around off, Oshada Fernando looks to defend off the front foot but gets an outside edge that runs down to third man. The batters come back for the second with ease.
BEATEN! Tossed up again, on a nagging length and outside off, Fernando presses forward and looks to defend but the ball just holds its line and goes past the outside edge.

FOUR BYES! Unlucky for the bowler! Nawaz bowls it slower and on a length around off, the ball grips and turns in sharply. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to give himself room but is completely beaten and the ball misses the leg stump as well. The ball eludes the keeper and runs away into the fence.
On a shorter length and this is played off the back foot towards mid-wicket for one.
SIX! A bit of aggression being shown here by Oshada Fernando and he gets maximum purchase. Flighted, on off, Fernando shimmies down the track and forces it over long off for a biggie.
Around off, blocked off.
Sliding into middle and leg, Fernando turns it through mid-wicket for a brace.
A bit of drift into the right-hander, solidly kept out on the off side by Fernando.
On off, Karunaratne knocks it down to long off for a single.
This is fuller and around off, Fernando strokes it away towards the cover region for another easy single.
Around off, Karunaratne drives it straight to the man at cover-point.
This is angled into off stump, Karunaratne strides forward and blocks it out.
A hint of flight, around off, Karunaratne blocks it from inside his crease.
A bit quicker and fired into middle, Karunaratne pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, angling in, Oshada Fernando blocks it to the off side.
SIX! Fifty up for Oshada Fernando and what a way to bring it up as well. This is floated on middle, Oshada Fernando shimmies down the pitch and lofts it over the long on fence for a biggie.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Fifty and Out for Oshada Fernando! Beautiful piece of bowling by Mohammad Nawaz and he draws first blood for Pakistan. Nicely flighted, with a bit of drift into the off stump. Fernando puts a big stride forward and looks to defend it onto the off side but the ball grips and turns, just enough to catch the outside edge. Mohammad Rizwan makes no mistake behind the stumps and a breezy innings from Fernando comes to an end. Nawaz is elated and Pakistan have a breakthrough before Lunch.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: Gives it some air this time and on off, Kusal Mendis goes on his back foot and blocks it to the off side.
Tossed up full and on off, Kusal Mendis knocks it to covers.
Floated around off, Kusal Mendis leans on and guides it towards point.
Tossed up on middle and off, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it to short covers.
Too full and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne gives himself some room and drills it to long off for a single.
Kusal Mendis gets off the mark. This is floated full on middle and leg, Kusal Mendis works it to long on for one.
Just short! Agha Salman darts this one on off, Dimuth Karunaratne goes to block it but only manages a thick inside edge. Luckily for him it did not carry to the short leg fielder.
Tossed up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne hits it back to the bowler. Good fielding by Agha Salman there.
On off, Dimuth Karunaratne knocks it towards the bowler again.
Floated on off, drifting in, Kusal Mendis plays a solid defense.
A bit short outside off, Kusal Mendis goes on his back foot and cuts it but straight to covers.
Too full and on middle, Kusal Mendis nudges it to mid-wicket.
On a length and around middle, Mendis defends it off the back foot.
Uppish but safe! Floats it up, outside off, Mendis looks to cover drive but gets a leading edge that falls well short of the man at extra cover.
On the pads, tucked to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Length, around off and this is punched towards mid off.

OUT! RUN OUT! An unfortunate way to depart but Kusal Mendis has to walk back. Tossed up from Agha Salman and around off, Dimuth Karunaratne makes a bit of room and pushes it firmly back towards the bowler. Salman manages to get a finger on it and the ball goes on to hit the stumps. Kusal Mendis is backing up and has to turn back quickly. The decision is sent upstairs and the third umpire has a good look at it. The bat is still in the air as the bails come off and Mendis is sent back as Pakistan end the session on a high. That will also be Lunch on Day 1.
Howout: run out (Agha Salman)

Commentary: Quicker and flatter around off, Dimuth Karunaratne knocks it to covers.
Tossed up on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it down the pitch.
Shortish and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne makes room and cut it through cover-point for a single.
Floated on off, Angelo Mathews stays back and defends it onto the ground.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne works it to short leg on the back foot.
Tossed up on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes this to the leg side.
Gives it some air on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne uses his feet and takes it on the full but only manages to hit it back to the bowler.
On middle, blocked out.
FOUR! Nice shot! A bit short by Nawaz on off, Dimuth Karunaratne makes room by going to the leg side and punches it of his back foot through extra covers for a boundary. 100 up for Sri Lanka.
Full and on middle and leg, Dimuth Karunaratne gets to the pitch of the ball and forces it to long on for one.
Slower and a bit shorter, well outside off, this is punched in front of square on the off side for a single.
Trying to turn it into the pads but spills it down leg, Mathews leaves it alone.
FOUR! Too easy for the batter. Way too short and outside off, Angelo Mathews punches it through the vacant extra cover region and picks up a boundary.
Drifted onto the pads, this is turned through square leg for a single.
A bit flatter and on off, Karunaratne blocks it out.
On the shorter side once again and on leg stump, Karunaratne just eases it in front of mid-wicket and picks up a couple of runs.
Full and around off, stroked away towards mid off.
Nicely drifted into the pads, Mathews nudges it away onto the leg side.
A touch of flight, around off, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Missed opportunity! This is way too short and wide, Angelo Mathews fails to cut it through cover-point.
Quicker and flatter, around off, Mathews taps it towards point.
On a shorter length again and around leg stump, Angelo Mathews uses his wrists to tuck it 'round the corner for a brace.
Starts off with a juicy full toss and almost picks up a wicket. This is around off, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to play it through mid on but ends up slicing it wide of mid off for a single.
Good turn! Pushed through a bit quicker and fuller on leg stump, the ball turns away but Mathews does well to keep it out.

EDGED AND FOUR! Excellent piece of bowling from Yasir Shah, flights it up around middle and the ball turns away sharply. Angelo Mathews looks to work it against the turn and gets an outside edge that goes past the diving fielder at first slip and into the third man fence.
Flighted once again, on a length and this time Mathews makes a solid block.
A bit of drift into middle and leg, Mathews defends it out.
Nice bit of loop now and bowled around leg stump, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Flatter trajectory, angled into middle, Karunaratne goes deep in his crease and eases it towards mid-wicket.
Floated up on middle, Karunaratne uses his feet and pushes it down to long on to turn the strike over.
Good running! Full and outside off, Angelo Mathews reaches out and pushes it towards mid off. Mathews calls early for a single and they get it with ease.
A tad shorter and sliding onto the pads, Karunaratne looks to flick off the back foot but fails to get it away.
On a good length and around middle, Karunaratne blocks it off the back foot.
Short again and outside off, Karunaratne bends his back and cuts it towards deep point for just a single.
Shah comes from around the stumps and goes wide of the crease to angle it into middle stump. Karunaratne stays solid in defense.
On a length and turning it in from around off, Karunaratne nudges it to the left of the bowler.
Cheeky attempt! Goes fuller and around off, Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the reverse sweep but misses and gets it off the pads towards silly point.
Around middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Slower this time and the length is pulled back too, the ball turns in a long way from around off but Karunaratne blocks it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! A very smart catch from Naseem Shah and the Sri Lankan skipper departs. This is full and floated up around off, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to negotiate the turn by playing the cheeky reverse sweep again but this time he pays the price. Karunaratne makes a decent connection but gets it a bit uppishly to the right of point. Naseem Shah over there takes a good low catch diving to his right and Yasir Shah gets a wicket early in his first spell. Sri Lanka are now three down and Pakistan right on top here.
Howout: c Naseem Shah b Yasir Shah

Commentary: Tossed up on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it down the pitch.
Full and on off, Angelo Mathews drives it to mid off.
Flighted delivery on off, Angelo Mathews leans on and defends it to the off side.
Darted on leg, Angelo Mathews tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Full again and down the leg, Angelo Mathews works it towards square leg for one.
A misfield and Dinesh Chandimal gets off the mark. This is floated full on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it straight to covers but there is a misfield and he gets a single.
Flighted on off, turning away Dinesh Chandimal punches it of his back foot to covers.
Tossed up on off, turning away a bit too much, Dinesh Chandimal offers no shot at it.
Tip and run. Shah bowls it full and on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to mid off with soft hands and gets across for a quick single.
Short and outside off, Angelo Mathews cuts it off his back foot past point for a single.
Good leave. Shah floats it up on off, turning away a bit, Dinesh Chandimal thinks about playing it at first but decides against it.
Shorter in length on off, Dinesh Chandimal guides it to point.
A bit short outside off, Angelo Mathews cuts it hard but straight to point. Missed oppurtunity.
Tossed up on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it back to the bowler.
Bowls it slow and on middle and leg, Angelo Mathews again is solid in his defense.
Full and around off, Angelo Mathews knocks it towards mid off.
Darts this one on leg, Angelo Mathews tucks it past short leg. He wants the single but Dinesh Chandimal refuses.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Angelo Mathews punches it of his back foot towards cover-point.
Almost for Yasir Shah. He bowls a flipper on middle, skids into the batter after hitting the surface. Dinesh Chandimal is late in his attemptd block and gets an inside edge onto his body.
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it to the offside.
Quicker and flatter on middle, Dinesh Chandimal plays for the turn but only manages an inside edge past the short leg. They cross.
Good bowling by Shah. This is again nicely tossed up on off, Angelo Mathews has to reach for it and hits it towards mid off/
Short and outside off, Angelo Mathews punches it through cover-point for one.
Floated on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to mid on for a run.
Slower through the air on off, Dinesh Chandimal opens the face of his bat and guides it to point.
Flatter delivery on off, Dinesh Chandimal works it to mid off, he wants the single but Angelo Mathews is not interested and sends him back.
Tossed up around off, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it to covers.
A bit short on off, Dinesh Chandimal stays back and defends it to the off side.
On off, kept out.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Chandimal. This is short and wide outside off, Dinesh Chandimal gives himself room and cuts it through the vacant cover-point region for a boundary.
This is very full, on middle, a low full toss. Mathews wrists it well in front of square on the leg side and picks up a single.
Nicely drifted onto middle and leg, Chandimal keeps it out.
Shorter in length and around off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to cut off the back foot but can't get it through cover-point.
Nicely bowled! Yasir Shah gets it to drift into the pads and turn away, Chandimal just about gets an inside edge onto the pads and that saves him from getting caught plumb in front.
Full and on leg stump, Chandimal plays it against the turn and towards wide mid on for one.
Excellent running! Tossed up on off, Mathews drives it towards mid off and races across for a run.
Flatter trajectory and angling it into leg stump, Angelo Mathews goes on the back foot and works it towards mid-wicket.
Floated up on middle, Mathews leans forward and defends it out.
Flatter again and around off, this is punched off the back foot but straight towards cover.
Very well flighted, sliding in from outside off. Mathews keeps it out off the front foot.
Goes a bit fuller and floats it up on the pads, Mathews plays it with soft hands to the right of the bowler.
A maiden! This is around off, Mathews strokes it away to extra cover.
On a nagging length and turning away from off stump, Dinesh Chandimal goes on the back foot to work it through covers for a single.
Nicely flighted, on off stump, Mathews reaches forward to defend.
Easily done! On a shorter length and around leg stump, Angelo Mathews turns it off the back foot past the diving fielder at mid-wicket and comes back for the third.

On off, this is driven towards mid off and the batters think about the run but decide against it. The keeper, Mohammad Rizwan seems a bit unhappy with the fielder and urges him to have a shy at the stumps if there's a chance.
Around off, blocked off the front foot.

EDGED AND FOUR! Yasir Shah floats it up full and pushes it wide of the off pole, Dinesh Chandimal throws his hands at it and gets a bottom edge. The ball nutmegs the keeper and runs down to the fence for a fortunate boundary.

Starts off the new spell with a no ball! This is on a fuller length and on off stump, Angelo Mathews stays solid in defense. Pakistan bowlers have been found guilty of overstepping every now and then.
On a good length and over middle, Mathews just tucks it away past mid-wicket and picks up a couple of runs.
A tad bit short and angled at the body, Angelo Mathews works it nicely off his hips down to deep backward square leg for two more.
Goes full and wide now, Mathews drives it straight towards mid off.
Length, around the top of off, Mathews hangs back and dabs it down on the leg side.
Delivers it on a hard length and around middle but the ball stays on the lower side, comfortably tucked away to mid-wicket by Mathews.
Right around the top of off and with good pace behind it. Angelo Mathews covers the line well and solidly defends it out.
Tossed up on off, Chandimal plays it with the turn towards the cover region.
A bit quicker and fuller, around middle, Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out.
Slows it up now and flights it on off stump, Dinesh Chandimal just caresses it towards covers.
Drops it a bit short now and offers some width as well, Chandimal cuts it to the man at sweeper cover for a single.
Drifts it onto middle, very full and turning away, Mathews plays it towards extra cover.
Flatter this time, around off, this is punched off the back foot towards extra cover.
Good length on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to gully.
Pulls his length back on middle, angling in, Dinesh Chandimal stays back and knocks it towards mid off.
Goes full this time and on off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it straight to mid off again.
Tight from Shah. This is on a hard length around off, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it off his back foot to short covers.

FOUR! Streaky but they all count. This is closer to the full length and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal slashes at it and gets an outside edge past the second slip fielder and races away to the fence. It is also called a no ball for overstepping.

Sharp bounce! Shah bowls it a bit short on middle and off, it bounces of the surface. Dinesh Chandimal looks to cut it but ends up getting hit on the top of his handle. He dropped his bat in all of this.
Short and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to covers.
Tossed up on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it out.
Shortish and outside off, Angelo Mathews punches it towards point.
FOUR! Good shot! Shah flights this on middle, Angelo Mathews dances down the track and smears it through the line over mid off for a boundary.
Floated on off, Angelo Mathews knocks it to the off side.
Tossed up full on middle, Angelo Mathews gets forward and pushes it to extra covers.
Quicker delivery and drifting onto the pads, Angelo Mathews again blocks it out well.
On a length and on off. Dinesh Chandimal strokes it towards covers.
Full delivery around off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it straight to mid off. The runs are slowing down.
Just short! Shah bangs in a short ball on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal pulls it awkwardly towards fine leg. The ball goes up in the air and falls just in front of fine leg. They cross.
Length delivery on off. Angelo Mathews pushes it to covers.
Pulls his length back a bit and on middle and leg, Angelo Mathews stays back and tucks it to the leg side.
Slower bouncer from Shah. He bowls this around off, Angelo Mathews goes for the pull but he is through with it very early and only manages to inside edge it onto his boots.

Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal drills it towards mid off and calls for the single. Angelo Mathews responds and they get across. The mid off fielder misses his shy at the non-striker's end, it looked close if would have hit the stumps.
Floated on off, Angelo Mathews knocks it to the off side.
Almost on a yorker length, on middle, Angelo Mathews digs it out to mid on.
A bit short on middle and leg, Angelo Mathews stays back and pushes it to mid on.
Tossed up full and on off, Angelo Mathews eases it towards long off for one.
Short and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it past point for a run.
FOUR! HAMMERED! This is full and wide putside off, Dinesh Chandimal holds his position and smashes it through extra covers for a boundary.
A bit short and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal punches it of his back foot but staright to covers.
Sharp bouncer! Shah bangs this short and on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
Good-length delivery on middle, angling in, Dinesh Chandimal tucks it to mid-wicket.
Shah uses the off cutter this time. He bowls it on a length and around off, nips back in a bit, Dinesh Chandimal reads it well and blocks it onto the ground.
Length delivery again and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it towards covers.
On off, blocked out.
Flighted and full, on the pads, Mathews tucks it to the man at short leg.
Looped up, around leg, turning away off the deck. Angelo Mathews stays back and blocks it out.
Floated and full, on off. Angelo Mathews strides forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, outside off. Angelo Mathews pushes it to mid off for a single.
A dot to end the over. It is tossed up, on the leg stump. Dinesh Chandimal stays back to block it out. Just a single off the over.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is full and on off. Angelo Mathews drives it down the ground, beats the bowlers and finds the boundary at long off.
Length and on off, defended out.
Short ball, around off, nips in a touch. Mathews stays back to block it out.
Length ball, on off, defended out.
A length ball, angled down leg. Angelo Mathews misses his flick. It goes down leg.
A delivery with great pace on it. It is served on a length, around middle. Angelo Mathews blocks it back to the bowler.
On off, blocked out.
Floated and full, outside off. Chandimal pushes it to cover for a single.
Looped up, around off, it turns away after landing. Angelo Mathews stays back and punches it to long on for an easy single.
Floated and full, on off. Dinesh Chandimal defends it out on his front foot.
It is flatter, on the pads. Dinesh Chandimal tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
Full and on the pads, Angelo Mathews nudges it to mid-wicket.

A bit of confusion but no trouble. It is full and on off. Dinesh Chandimal drives it towards mid on. Angelo Mathews ventures out looking for a single but was sent back. Dinesh Chandimal makes it in time.
Length ball, outside off, defended out.
Good length, on off. Dinesh Chandimal punches it through covers for a brace.
Fraction short, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal gets on his toes and punches it to covers.

FOUR! Too wide and punished. A full-length delivery, wide outside off. Dinesh Chandimal expands his arms and slashes it through cover-point. It was in the air but it goes through the gap and into the boundary.
A slower delivery to end the over. A cutter, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal strides forward and blocks it watchfully.
Looped up, on off, blocked out.
Touch short, on off. Angelo Mathews pushes it to covers.
On off, blocked out solidly.
Floated and full, outside off. Angelo Mathews drives it through covers for a single.
Floated and full, on leg. Dinesh Chandimal is a bit early in closing the face of the blade. It goes to the off side off the outside edge.
Tossed up, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal smothers it out. Only a single off the over. Pakistan would be desperate to break this stand now which has started to bother them.
Outside off, left alone by Mathews.
Length ball, outside off yet again. Angelo Mathews coves his stumps and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Touch fuller, on the fifth stump. Angelo Mathews gets forward and drives it on the up towards mid off, not in the gap.
Back of a length, outside off, nips in a touch. Angelo Mathews does not bother it.
An inswinger this time, full and on off. Angelo Mathews hits it towards mid on. Five dots now.
Hasan Ali records his second maiden of the innings. He ends the over with an outswinger which is left alone by Mathews.
Floated, outside off, turning away. Dinesh Chandimal lets it through.
Full, on fourth stump. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to cover for a quick single.
On off, driven to short extra cover.
Tossed up, around off. Mathews taps it to point.

DROPPED! Babar Azam cannot believe it while Nauman Ali looks at the skies. The captain has put down a crucial catch. Floated and full, around off. Angelo Mathews is very early into his stroke. He drives it on the up towards covers. Babar Azam takes a step to his left to get to the ball but it does not stick. Angelo Mathews gets a lifeline in his 100th Test match.
Full and on off. Angelo Mathews pushes it out.
Length ball, on off, defended out.
Full length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal drives it to covers. He ventures out looking for a single but Angelo Mathews says there is no run there.
This is full, outside off, shaping in a touch. Dinesh Chandimal drives it to covers on the front foot but does not find the gap.
Length ball, on the stumps. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it to the leg side.
Dinesh Chandimal drives this full length delivery to covers.
An attempted yorker, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal taps it to point. A maiden to end the afternoon session. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1.
Ali starts off on a length and around off, Mathews goes back and across to push it towards cover.
Nice flighted, around middle and leg, Mathews blocks it off the front foot.
A hint of turn on this occasion. Just drops the length a bit short and on off, the ball turns away as Mathews caresses it through the cover region for a single.
Floated up, around off, Chandimal drives it towards sweeper cover for one more.
Well bowled! Drifted onto middle and leg and this is fuller as well, Angelo Mathews strides forward and keeps it out.
On a nagging length and pushed through a bit on off stump. Angelo Mathews goes on the back foot and eases it towards covers.
On the shorter side and close to the off pole, Dinesh Chandimal goes deep in his crease to punch it through cover for a single.
On a good length, Mathews eases it off the back foot to sweeper cover for one more.
A bit quicker and on the pads, Chandimal nudges it onto the leg side.
Tossed up on off, turning away a touch. Dinesh Chandimal defends it off the front foot.
A little bit of drift into the right-hander. This is around leg stump and Chandimal does well to keep it out.
Darts this one into middle stump but Dinesh Chandimal is able to block it onto the off side.
Fuller and around off, Mathews eases it towards covers.
Nicely flighted, on a nagging length and on off, Mathews opens the face of the blade and pushes it towards cover-point.
This is floated up on leg stump, Angelo Mathews works it towards short mid-wicket.
A tad quicker and on a length, Mathews solidly blocks it off.
Slowed up on this occasion, around off stump, this is defended off the front foot.

A maiden but it is pretty easy for the batters at the moment to play at every delivery. Gives it a lot more air and bowls it on off stump, Angelo Mathews looks for the expansive cover drive but just punches it towards extra cover.
On middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it under his eyeline.
Shorter in length and outside off, this is played off the back foot through covers for an easy single.
Tosses it up on the pads, Mathews blocks it out.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Tossed up on off, Angelo Mathews thumps it right back over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Just short! Yasir Shah overcompensates and drags it down, offering width as well. Angelo Mathews rocks back but mistimes the cut shot on the bounce to the point fielder.
Flatter delivery, around middle, Mathews pushes it back towards the bowler.
On a length and around off, this is eased away towards covers.
Nicely drifted onto middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal defends it out with soft hands.
Flatter delivery, on off. This is defended back to the bowler.
A bit fuller this time and around off, Chandimal presses forward and drives it towards extra cover.
Floated up, on the fourth stump line and this is strokes away towards cover.
Around middle and leg, this is worked well in front square on the leg side for a single.
On a length and angling into the pads, Chandimal backs away a bit and pushes it towards mid on.
Pushed through a bit quicker and on off, easily blocked off by Chandimal.
Yasir Shah doing a good job of getting Dinesh Chandimal bogged down. This is around middle and leg, Chandimal defends it out.
Around off, Chandimal looks to drive it through covers but fails to get it through.

FOUR! Just over! Yasir Shah releases all the pressure by dragging it down. Dinesh Chandimal pulls it off the back foot but without much timing, just clearing Imam-ul-Haq at short mid-wicket. The ball goes away into the fence.
A hint of flight, around off, Chandimal caresses it towards extra cover.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A sharp take by Mohammad Rizwan behind the stumps and Angelo Mathews is sent back to the hut! Mathews could not make the most of his extra life and slips out in his 40s. This is a classical slow left-armer's dismissal, beautifully flighted by Nauman Ali on a nagging length and a bit outside the off stump. The ball grips and turns away a bit as it is given a lot more air and Mathews has a little dab at it. The ball takes the outside edge and Rizwan does the rest. Mathews falls short of his fifty but gets back to a round of applause from the crowd and from his family as well.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Nauman Ali

Commentary: Slower through the air and floated up well outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva has a gentle push at it and edges it past the slip cordon for a couple of runs.
Nicely flighted on off stump, de Silva backs away and defends it towards cover.
Short and on off, punched to covers.
Angled into the pads, Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and blocks it out.
A bit quicker and fuller, angled onto middle. Dhananjaya de Silva tries to make room and cut but manages to defend it out.
Full and on leg. Dinesh Chandimal drives it to long off for an easy single.
Floated, on off stump. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it to cover.
Two dots in a row! Darted on the pads, Dhananjaya de Silva nudges it to short leg.
Floated and full, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it back to the bowler.
Make it four dots now! Tossed up, on off, turning away. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to drive it away but gets it to backward point off the outside edge.
On off, driven to the left of mid on. No run there.
Full, on leg, slower through the air. Dinesh Chandimal defends it back to the bowler on his front foot.
Quicker and full, on the stumps. Dinesh Chandimal remains solid in his defense.
Slower, wide outside off. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to point for a single.
On off, defended out.
Angled into the pads. Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and blocks it out watchfully.
Just a single off the over! It is flatter and quicker, around leg. Dhananjaya de Silva goes behind and pushes it towards mid off.
Fuller, on off. Chandimal drives it to covers but straight to the fielder.
Just short, wide outside off. Dinesh Chandimal gets on one knee and slashes it hard towards backward point. Fawad Alam dives to his right to make a sharp stop.
On off, pushed to mid off.
Flaoted and full, outside off. Chandimal drives it towards covers.
FOUR! This time he connects it sweetly. It is a full toss, on the bodyline. Dinesh Chandimal drives it down the ground. It races away to the long on fence.
Outside off, pushed to point.

FOUR! Dhananjaya de Silva now gets his first boundary of the innings. It is tossed up, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva dances down the track, gets to the pitch of the delivery and drills it past mid on for a boundary.

SIX! BANG! Dhananjaya de Silva using his feet really well here. It is floated and full, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva comes down the track and lofts it inside-out over mid off and sends it sailing over the fence.
On off, blocked out solidly.
Tossed up, on the stumps. Dhananjaya de Silva goes back and pushes it to cover.
Floated and full, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it out on his front foot.
Touch fuller, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva strides forward and drives it to long off for one. 11 runs come off this over. A great one for the hosts.
Floated and full, on off, it turns away a touch. Dhananjaya de Silva gets on his front foot and blocks it away.
On off, de Silva defends it out watchfully.
This one is on the pads, Dhananjaya de Silva goes back and flicks it to square leg for one.
Around off, defended out watchfully.
Fifty for Chandimal! Another top innings from him. It is short, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal punches it to deep cover for one.
Floated and full, outside off, defended to mid off.
Another single now as this pushed down to long off.
Looped up, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it on the front foot.
Darts it on the pads, Dhananjaya de Silva flicks it to square leg for a quick single.
This one lands outside off and turns away sharply. Dinesh Chandimal covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
Fuller, just outside off. Dinesh Chandimal gets on his front foot to block it out.
Short ball, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal rocks back and punches it to cover. Single taken. Three runs off the over.
Flighted and full, on the stumps. Dinesh Chandimal eases it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Lucky runs, but it does not matter how they come. It is full and on leg. Dinesh Chandimal gets low and drags his sweep over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length ball, around off, Chandimal punches it to point off the back foot.
NO BALL! This one is sprayed down leg. Dinesh Chandimal gets it to fine leg. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.
Loopy ball, down leg. Dinesh Chandimal pads it away.

SIX! Poor delivery and punished. It is a short ball, on the bodyline. Dinesh Chandimal opens his stance and pulls it to deep mid-wicket. The ball lands directly on the boundary cushions. It is a maximum.
A single now as this is worked through cover. Chandimal moves to 63.
Floated and full, just outside off. Chandimal drives it to extra cover on the front foot.
Tossed up, around off. Dinesh Chandimal taps it to point and scampers across for a quick single.
Slower through the air, outside off, tapped to point.
Quicker and on middle, blocked out sharply.
Flatter and on leg stump. Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and blocks it to mid on.
Full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets on his front foot to block it out.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
SIX! All the way! It is floated and full, on off. Dinesh Chandimal gets low and smacks it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
On off, pushed to covers.
Floated and full, outside off, it turns away with some extra bounce. Dinesh Chandimal looks to drive but misses. It goes to the man at first slip after hitting Rizwan's gloves. No trouble there.
On off, defended back to the bowler.
Length, on off. Chandimal pushes it to cover for one.
It is full, on the stumps. Dinesh Chandimal drives it to covers.
Full again, on off, some spin on offer. Dinesh Chandimal blocks it out watchfully.
Around off, defended out.
Outside off, pushed to covers yet again.

Floated and full, on off. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to cover and initially looks for a single, but he sends back in partner in no time. He makes a bad call but gives enough time for his partner to get back.
Full and on off. Chandimal gets it to mid-wicket off the inner half. They take a single now.
Tossed up full on middle, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it towards short mid off.
FOUR! Nice shot! This is a bit short and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal picks the length early and opens the face of his bat and guides it towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Slightly short again and on off, Dinesh Chandimal punches it through covers for one.
Floated full on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva hits it back to the bowler.
A bit short and around off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes on his back foot and blocks it to silly point.
Tossed up full on middle, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to short mid off.
Slower through the air on middle, Dinesh Chandimal leans on and defends it to the off side.
Shorter in length and on off, Dinesh Chandimal goes on his back foot and cuts it through cover-point for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Dhananjaya de Silva drives it towards mid off.
Short and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva guides it towards point from his back foot.
Darts this one on the leg stump, Dhananjaya de Silva goes down and sweeps it wide of the fine leg fielder and picks up two runs.
Flighted delivery on off, Dinesh Chandimal gives himself some room and pushes it towards point for a single.
Quicker and flatter on leg, Dhananjaya de Silva steps out of the crease and flicks it with his inner half towards deep square leg for a brace.
Short and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva cuts it towards point for one. There was some confusion between the batters but they complete the run at the end.
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it out.
Flighted on off, turning away a bit, Dinesh Chandimal watches it carefully and defends it well.
On middle, blocked out.
Flatter and around off, Dhananjaya de Silva defends it to the off side from his back foot.

FOUR! Easily done by de Silva. This is short and wide outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva waits for it and opens the face of his bat at the last moment. The ball races away towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva tucks it to mid on.
Floated on off, Dhananjaya de Silva again is solid in his defense.
Slightly short and around off, Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it to cover-point region for a quick single.
Bowls this full and sliding down the leg, Dinesh Chandimal goes down and sweeps it towards fine leg for one. 6 runs from the over.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mohammad Nawaz sends back the big fish, Dinesh Chandimal. This is nicely tossed up on off, Dinesh Chandimal dances down the track to heave it over mid on but goes through his shot early. The ball takes a top edge and goes straight into the hands of Fawad Alam who was stationed at point. Pakistan have got the opening they were after. Can they make the most of it?
Howout: c Fawad Alam b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: Niroshan Dickwella gets off the mark straightaway. Nawaz darts this one full and on off, Niroshan Dickwella drives it well through covers for a brace.
Floated on middle, Niroshan Dickwella knocks it past short leg.
Flighted on middle again, Niroshan Dickwella blocks it to the leg side.
Just short! This is floated on middle, turning in a bit, Niroshan Dickwella leans on to block it but plays it a bit uppishly. The ball falls just short of the short leg fielder.
On middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Nicely flighted, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it with soft hands towards silly point.
This is drifted into middle and leg, DDS blocks it out off the front foot.
Pulls back the length a bit and bowls it around middle and leg, de Silva goes on the back foot and pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated up on leg stump, de Silva strides forward to defend.
Flatter trajectory and sliding down leg, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to work it fine but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Too short and wide, Dhananjaya de Silva just hangs back and taps it through point for a boundary.
Fuller and at the stumps, Niroshan Dickwella gets inside the line of the ball and paddles it fine. The ball goes towards fine leg as Fawad Alam chases it down and keeps it down to a couple.
Around middle, this is paddled away through backward square leg for a single.
Switches to around the stumps to the right-hander and bowls it flatter, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva just eases it through covers and rotates the strike.
Back to over the wicket now and this is fuller, on off. Dickwella flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
On a nagging length, turning into middle, Dickwella presses forward and defends it out.
Drops it a bit short and bowls it around leg stump, Dickwella stylishly tucks it past square leg for a single.
On the shorter side and on off stump, Dickwella punches it down to long on and turns the strike over.
Beautifully bowled! Just holds it back a touch and drifts it on middle and leg, allowing the ball to grip and turn. Dhananjaya de Silva watches it all the way through and blocks it out.
Around off, this is pushed away towards cover.
Drop and run! A touch fuller and on off, DDS backs away and taps it towards cover-point to steal a quick run.
Just milking the singles here. Floated up, around off, Dickwella uses his feet to get to the pitch of the ball and just knocks it down to long on for one more.
Slower through the air and on off, de Silva keeps it out.
Lovely bowling! Flights it on a fuller length, around off and turning in. Dickwella looks to drive it against the turn but gets it off the inner half of the bat and back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Up and over! For a moment, the fielder at mid on thought he's in the game but no chance at all. Tossed up on middle and leg, Niroshan Dickwella skips down the track and lofts it with the turn, over wide mid on for a boundary.
On off, stroked through extra cover for a single.
Beaten! This is tossed up on a nagging length and on off stump, Mohammad Nawaz gets good turn and bounce off the pitch and Dhananjaya de Silva has no idea where the ball went.
On off, DDS blocks it off the front foot.
Floated up, around the off pole and this is flicked away towards mid-wicket.
Good length, turning into the off pole, enough time for Dickwella to get onto the back foot and punch it through covers for a single.
Full but a bit wide of the off stump, Dhananjaya de Silva lets it through to the keeper.
A bit of drift into the right-hander and it's been solidly blocked out by de Silva.

Cries of 'catch it,' from the keeper but the ball is in the air for just a short while. This is flighted and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva tries to go inside-out over covers but mistimes it towards sweeper cover and picks up a single.
Around leg stump, this is dabbed down towards short leg.

A huge appeal for LBW from the bowler but it is turned down! Floats it up around off stump, Niroshan Dickwella puts a big stride across and looks to sweep it away but misses and gets rapped on the pads. The keeper and the bowler both go up but pretty soon the keeper is content with the umpire's decision. The replay shows that the impact was a fair bit outside off stump. The bowler almost convinced Babar Azam to take the review but they ran out of time, which turned out better for Pakistan.
Short and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva easily cuts it of his back foot through point for one.
Flatter and quicker on middle, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it hard but straight to square leg.
SIX! Clean hit! This is tossed up on middle , Niroshan Dickwella dances down the track and smashes it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Gives it some air this time, on off, Niroshan Dickwella knocks it to the off side.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Niroshan Dickwella pushes it of his back foot towards short mid on.. Yasir Shah did well to stop it diving to his right.
FOUR! Good shot! This is short and on middle and leg, turning further down the leg, Niroshan Dickwella stays in his crease and flicks it towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
BEATEN! Naseem Shah starts with a length delivery outside off, shaping away a bit, Dhananjaya de Silva tries to slash at it from his crease but gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! TIMBER! Naseem Shah gets the breakthrough with the second new ball. This is a bit fuller in length and on middle, nips back in slightly, just a perfect inswinging delivery. Dhananjaya de Silva plays for the outswing without any footwork and gets beaten all ends up. The ball goes onto crash into the stumps. Sri Lanka six down now and are running out of batters.
Howout: b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Bowls it full and on off, Dunith Wellalage pushes it with inner half past short leg. They cross.

EDGED BUT DROPPED! It is Babar Azam again. Naseem Shah serves this full outside off, angling away, Niroshan Dickwella goes for the drive but gets an outside edge towards second slip. It goes quickly but at a comfortable height and Babar Azam drops another sitter in this innings.
FOUR! Nicely done! This is full again and on middle, Niroshan Dickwella smears it over mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Niroshan Dickwella. This time through the off side. It is fuller in length, outside off. Niroshan Dickwella reaches out and slashes it through the gap at point. It goes through the gap and into the boundary. The umpire also signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps. So, that brings up 300 for Sri Lanka.

JAFFA! Niroshan Dickwella gets squared up this time. Naseem Shah is bowling with fire here. It is on a length, around off, angled away from the left-hander. Niroshan Dickwella gets beaten on the outside edge and not by much.
This is on a length and down the leg, Dunith Wellalage misses his flick and the ball goes to the keeper.
On a length and outside off, Dunith Wellalage guides it through backward point for a single.
Good length on middle, Niroshan Dickwella tucks it away to square leg.

BEATEN! Hasan Ali with some extra bounce there. He bowls it on a hard length and on middle and off, skidding through. Niroshan Dickwella goes for the cut but gets beaten by the bounce and it goes past the outside edge
Back of a length and on middle, Niroshan Dickwella works it to square leg.
Short and wide outside off, Niroshan Dickwella cuts it in front of square and picks up three runs.
This is great bowling by Shah. He bowls it on a length and on off, angling away, Niroshan Dickwella tries to poke at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and around off, Niroshan Dickwella knocks it towards mid off.
Tight from Shah. This is on a length and on off, Niroshan Dickwella moves across and pushes it to mid off.
Well watched. Shah goes fuller and outside off, Niroshan Dickwella offers no shot at it.
Sharp bouncer! Shah bangs in a short ball on middle and leg, Niroshan Dickwella does well to get out of the way.
Fullish delivery and outside off, Niroshan Dickwella works it past point for a single. He will keep the strike.
FOUR! This is poor bowling by Ali. He bowls it short and wide outside off, Niroshan Dickwella uses the pace of the ball and cuts it behind point for a cracking boundary.
On a length and on off, Niroshan Dickwella knocks it towards mid off.
Hasan Ali goes full and outside off, inviting the drive. But Niroshan Dickwella leaves it alone.
Good length around off, Niroshan Dickwella gets on top of it and flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Hasan Ali goes round the wicket and bowls it full outside off, angling in, Niroshan Dickwella lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.

NOT OUT! Hasan Ali appeals for lbw but the umpire denies. Babar Azam takes the review but it does not go their way. It is full, straying down leg. Niroshan Dickwella stays back and tries to flick it away but misses. He gets rapped on his pads. Ali thinks he has got his man here and convinces the skipper to take the review. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing leg stump. Niroshan Dickwella survives.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! What a shot from the debutant! Length again, around the top of off, Wellalage stands tall and punches it through covers for a boundary, his first ever in Test cricket.
Good comeback by Naseem Shah! Goes for the short ball and angles it around the helmet of the batter, Wellalage does well to sway away from the line of the ball.
Naseem Shah now follows up a boundary with two dots on the trot. It is wide outside off, on a fuller length. Dunith Wellalage leaves it alone.
Length ball, on off, defended out solidly.
Good length, on off. Dunith Wellalage gets behind the line and blocks it out solidly.
Starts off with a fullish delivery in that channel around the off stump and slanting across. Niroshan Dickwella makes an assured leave.
Ali goes fuller and drifts onto the pads, Dickwella flicks it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Good length, keeps it around the top of off, Dunith Wellalage hangs back and dabs it down towards backward point.
Pitches it up this time on off stump, Wellalage gets across and defends it out with a straight bat.
Length ball, angling across the left-hander, Wellalage pushes it out towards point.
Ali goes full and tries to attack the pads, Wellalage eases it in front of square on the leg side for a run.
Shah starts off with a length ball and slants it well across the off stump, Wellalage lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball, around leg stump and just nipping back into the left-hander, Wellalage nudges it onto the leg side.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Full and wide, allowing the batter to free his arms and Dunith Wellalage crunches it past point for the first boundary of the day.
Back of a length, over off, Wellalage hops onto the back foot and keeps it out.
A touch fuller and on off, Wellalage blocks it onto the off side.
Naseem Shah switches to around the wicket and angles it into the off pole, Dunith Wellalage stays solid in defense.

FOUR! Hasan Ali tries to rattle the batter with a short ball but just doesn't get it short enough. This is over middle and leg, Niroshan Dickwella pulls it off the back foot and finds the square leg fence.
Good length, outside off and left alone.
A touch fuller and around off, Dickwella pushes it towards mid off.
Keeps it on a fullish length and spills it way down leg, Dickwella leaves it alone and it's a good take down to his right by the keeper Mohammad Rizwan.
Short of a length and on the pads, this is tucked away off his pads by Niroshan Dickwella down to fine leg for a couple of runs. With that, Dickwella moves on to 49.

Ali comes from around the wicket now and angles it in from wide of the crease. It is on a good length and angling in a long way from around off, Dickwella looks to play at it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.

OUT! CAUGHT! Naseem Shah with a spicy bouncer and he has got the early breakthrough for Pakistan! Shah keeps coming from around the wicket and angles in a short ball at 136 clicks. The ball is bowled at a decent height but it is the line that has done the trick. The ball is angled in towards the body and Dunith Wellalage tries his best to bend his back and sway away from the line of the ball. The ball goes off the gloves and pops up around the gully region. Babar Azam attacks it from the slip cordon and takes a simple catch.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Back to over the wicket now for the right-hander. This is full and straight, Ramesh Mendis makes a solid front foot block.
A touch fuller and around off, Mendis defends it towards cover.
Another bumper, this time over middle. Mendis ducks under it well. Naseem Shah has overstepped and a no ball is called.
Length ball, around middle, Mendis presents a dead bat at it.
Good heat from Naseem Shah and he seems to have his tail up now. Pacy bumper, around off and this one bounces a bit extra. Ramesh Mendis sways his head away from the line of the ball.
Around the top of off, Mendis bunts it out on the off side.

Drop and run! Yet another FIFTY for Niroshan Dickwella, his 22nd in Test cricket. Length ball, angled into off stump from around the wicket, Dickwella just plays it with soft hands towards short cover and races through for a single. It will be interesting to see how Dickwella goes about his business from here on.
Length ball, around off, Mendis blocks it out.
Length again, slanted into middle and off, Mendis pushes it out onto the off side.
Full length and on off, Ramesh Mendis drives it towards mid off.
Full once again from Ali, Ramesh Mendis knocks it towards covers.
Serves this one on a length and on off. Ramesh Mendis blocks it to the off side.
On a good length and just angling across the off stump, Dickwella hangs back and opens the face of the bat to guide it towards third man for a run.
Just pitched up a bit and around off, Mendis gets behind the line to make the block.
Fuller and outside off, Ramesh Mendis comes forward and pushes it gently towards wide mid off.

Mendis is off the mark! Length ball, around off, Mendis edges it down with soft hands and the ball goes through backward point. Hasan Ali from point chases it down and slides in to pull the ball back inside. Good work from the fielder and the batters come back for the third with ease.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A loose shot from Niroshan Dickwella and Naseem Shah gets the double-strike! Just short of a length and close to the leg pole, it is there to be pulled. Dickwella looks to swivel-pull it fine but gets strangled down the leg side and ends up getting an edge on it. The ball goes through to the keeper Mohammad Rizwan who takes a simple catch and Dickwella has to depart after reaching his half-century. Pakistan just a couple of wickets away now from bundling out the opposition.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Length ball, slanted into middle, Prabath Jayasuriya hangs back and keeps it out. End of another fruitful over by Naseem Shah, 4 runs and a wicket off it.
This is banged in short and over off stump, Ramesh Mendis ducks under it well.
Length, around off, Mendis pushes it off the front foot and squeezes it through extra cover for a quick single.
Fuller in length and attacking the stumps, Jayasuriya defends it under his eyeline.

Jayasuriya has no idea what happened there! A nasty short ball, over off stump. Jayasuriya looks to get behind the line of the ball but gets hurried on and takes a blow on the fingers, which can be a sore one. The physio is out to have a look, hope he is fine.
Back of a length, around middle and this time there's no extra bounce. Jayasuriya manages to defend it back onto the deck.
Good running! Around middle and leg, Jayasuriya works it towards wide mid on and scampers through for a quick single.
A length ball, angling into middle, Jayasuriya works it off the inner half of the bat towards square leg and rotates the strike.
Goes full and straight now, Mendis drives it towards mid on.
This is bowled a bit wide of the off stump, Mendis defends it out with soft hands.

FOUR! Edged away! Naseem Shah lets out a huge gasp and he cannot believe it. Shah comes from around the wicket and slides one across the off stump. Ramesh Mendis has a dab at it and gets a bottom edge past the keeper and into the fence.
Good short ball! This is dug in at good pace and height, over middle. The ball flies through around head height as Mendis ducks under it.
No ball! Banged in short again and over leg stump, Ramesh Mendis with another good duck. Once again a Pakistani bowler oversteps and a no ball is called.
Similar to the previous delivery, short and around leg stump, Mendis just ducks under it.
This is dug in short and angled onto middle, Jayasuriya bends his back and sways away from it as the ball goes pretty close to the gloves on its way through to the keeper.
Back of a length and around off, left alone by Jayasuriya.
This is angled down leg and Jayasuriya shoulders arms to it.
Solid stroke from Jayasuriya! Pitched up around off, Jayasuriya punches it on the up and straight down the ground. Imam-ul-Haq from mid off chases it down as the batters get back for the third.
This is a bit fuller and just nipping back into middle stump, Mendis looks to work it leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads. There's a stifled appeal from the bowler but nothing is given.
A good bumper, this is over off and at a difficult height for the batter. Ramesh Mendis has a think about taking it on but pulls out at the last moment.
Back of a length delivery from 'round the wicket, on middle, Prabath Jayasuriya pushes it towards silly point and gets across for a quick single.
Short and on middle, angling in, Ramesh Mendis awkwardly pulls it away towards deep square leg as the ball did not bounce that much.They cross.
On a length and around off, Prabath Jayasuriya knocks it towards point for a run.
Fullish delivery on middle, Ramesh Mendis covers his stump and blocks it to mid on.
Slower ball from from Shah, on a length and off, Ramesh Mendis drives it through covers for another single.
Shah serves a fuller one from 'over the wicket, on middle, angling in. Prabath Jayasuriya makes room and drives it straight to mid on.
Yasir Shah starts with almost a yorker length delivery, Ramesh Mendis digs it out towards long on for a run.

An appeal for LBW but turned down. This is tossed up on middle and leg, Prabath Jayasuriya leans on to block it but misses it and gets hit on the pads. The fielders appeal for the LBW but the finger stays down.
A bit short and outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya guides it to point.
Floated full on middle, Prabath Jayasuriya steps out and drill it towards mid on for a single.
Shortish and outside off, Ramesh Mendis stays back and punches it through covers and picks up three runs.

OUT! LBW! Well, well, well. Pakistan have won the battle. Cannot really blame the umpire for not giving this out initially as the batter was way too far down the track. This is flatter around middle and leg, Prabath Jayasuriya comes down the track to block it but his bat gets stuck behind his back pad. He gets rapped on the pads and Yasir is up in elation. Yes, it was not even an appeal. Shah is confident that the batsman is out. Now, it is interesting to see Kumar Dharmasena's reaction. He stays still as a stone, almost waiting for Yasir to plead on his knees and then shakes his head after what seems a century, indicating that the batsman was far too forward. Shah looks at Rizwan and Babar, with the keeper smiling. He agrees it looks close but also cautions Babar that this might be a case of height as the batsman was way down the crease. Babar looks at the keeper and bowler, smiles and then takes the review. No point in checking UltraEdge but the protocols must be followed. Well, does not take much time to show that there is no bat involved. Now, the Ball Tracking. Where is the impact? IN LINE! Well, well, well. And checking further, it projects the ball to be hitting the stumps. In what seems like a rarity, Dharmasena has to reverse his decision! He rarely has to, he is that good an umpire. Well, Yasir has struck in his first over of the day and Pakistan are now a wicket away from batting.
Howout: lbw b Yasir Shah

Commentary: Full length, outside off, driven to sweeper cover.
Full length, on the stumps. Mendis plays the on drive and works it towards long on. The batters run the first one hard. They look for the second run but decide against it.

FOUR! Incredible shot! Asitha Fernando gets off the mark with a boundary. Naseem serves it full and on off. Asitha Fernando opens the face of the blade and guides it through the gap at backward point for four.
A sharp bouncer now, Fernando ducks under it.

Naseem Shah makes an appeal for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. Shah convinces his skipper and they go for the review. It is a full toss, angling down leg. Asitha Fernando crouches inside the crease and gets hit on his thigh. The Ball Tracking confirms that the ball is missing the wickets. Asitha Fernando gets some more time to spend at the crease.
Full length, on off. Fernando pushes it to cover.
Floated and full, on off. Mendis blocks it out on his front foot.
Touch quicker, on off. Mendis fends it to covers.

NOT OUT! Ramesh Mendis survives! He uses the review wisely here. It is tossed up, on leg stump. Mendis goes for the sweep. He does not connect cleanly. The ball brushes his pads and goes to fine leg. Yasir Shah appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. The review is taken by Mendis in no time. The UltraEdge confirms that Mendis got his glove on it. The original decision has to be overturned.
A single now as this is pushed through covers.
Lovely bowling! Nice bit of flight, drifted into middle, the ball grips and turns away sharply. Asitha Fernando looks to defend off the front foot but is beaten all ends up.

What is Asitha Fernando trying to do here? This is a bit dragged down and turning away from middle stump. Fernando rocks back and looks to pull against the turn. Fernando gets nowhere near the ball and the ball goes agonizingly over the off stump.
Starts off with a flatter delivery, down leg, Mendis looks to paddle it fine but misses and gets hit on the pads.
This is short and wide, Mendis rocks back and punches it towards sweeper cover, no run taken.

FOUR! A valiant effort in the deep but it will be a boundary. Tossed up, around middle, Mendis gets down low and sweeps it behind square on the leg side. The fielder from deep square leg runs to his right and puts in the dive but can't stop the boundary.

FOUR! And again! Useful runs here for Sri Lanka from the bat of Ramesh Mendis. Darted onto middle and leg, Mendis sweeps and sweeps fine, gets it well behind square and there's no chance for the fielder this time.
Drifted onto the pads, this is eased away onto the leg side for an easy single. Very smart batting this from Ramesh Mendis.
Length, drifted into middle and leg, Fernando keeps it out.
Slower through the air and looped up on a length, Mendis keeps it out.
Tosses it up now, on the stumps, Mendis blocks it out.
This is full and straight, kept out once again.
Nicely flighted, around middle and leg, Mendis gets forward well to defend it out.
SIX! BIG ONE! It is full and outside off. Mendis gets down on one knee and slogs it over the long on fence for a biggie.
FOUR! 10 runs in two balls to end the over. It is tossed up, on the pads. Mendis gets low and drags his sweep past the fine leg fielder for a boundary.
Full, on off, blocked out.
Floated and full, on off. Fernando blocks it out.
It is slower through the air. Lands outside off and turns away. No shot on offer.
On off, blocked out solidly.
Full and on off. Fernando blocks it out on the front foot.
A maiden for Nawaz, Fernando does well see off the over. It is full and on the stumps. Fernando gets forward to block it out.
Flatter, outside off. Mendis guides it towards point.
Floated and full, on off. Mendis blocks it back to the bowler on the front foot.
Fuller, around middle. Mendis eases it back.
Loopy ball, full and on off. Mendis goes back and pushes it to cover.
Outside off, pushed to the off side.

OUT! TIMBER! Quicker one does the trick for Yasir Shah and he picks up his third wicket of the innings. It is pushed through quicker, on fourth stumps, turns in a touch. Mendis is caught inside his crease and ends up playing all around it. The ball goes through to rattle the stumps. Pakistan have bowled out Sri Lanka for 378.
Howout: b Yasir Shah

Commentary: Asitha Fernando gets a bit on curve straightaway. It is a length ball, outside off, shaping away off the deck. Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone for the keeper.

OUT! CLEANED UP! It is the line and the length that is key here. Abdullah Shafique the hero of the previous game walks back on a duck. It is a length ball, on fourth stump, just shaping away a touch. Abdullah Shafique does not move his feet and tries to poke at it from inside the crease but ends up playing the wrong line. The ball takes the inside edge and disturbs the stumps. Asitha Fernando is pumped up with this early wicket and so are the fans in Galle.
Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Good length, outside off, some extra bounce this time. Azam stays back and blocks it out watchfully.
Babar Azam and Pakistan are off the mark! It is a length ball, on the pads, Azam stays back and flicks it through square leg. They take two before the fielder cuts it out.
Asitha Fernando serves it on a length, just outside off, it hurries onto the batter and nips in as well. Babar Azam fails to defend it out. It goes to the man at third slip off the thigh pad.
Much straighter this time, on the pads. Azam stays back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single. Three runs and a wicket off the first over. The hosts are off to a bright start.
Tossed up, on the pads, Azam looks to clip but misses. He gets rapped on his pads. Prabath Jayasuriya appeals for lbw but the umpire says no. Might be going down leg.

NOT OUT! A complete waste of a review from Sri Lanka, very early in the innings as well. This is dragged down and angled in from well outside off. Babar Azam skips down the track and looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Huge appeal for lbw from behind the stumps and also from the bowler, but the umpire is unmoved. After a lot of discussion, Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the review. UltraEdge shows that there's no bat involved but Ball Tracking shows that the impact is both, over 3 meters and outside off. Babar survives.
Three dots in a row! It is floated and full, on off. Azam blocks it into the deck on the front foot.
Make that four! Fuller, outside off. Azam strides forward and blocks it out.
Short ball, outside off. Azam looks to pull it away but finds the fielder at mid on.
FOUR! It is short again and Azam does not miss out this time. Shorter, on middle and leg. Azam uses the depth of the crease and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full length, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq punches it to covers.
Asitha Fernando dishes it full, on leg stump. Imam-ul-Haq does enough to block it back to the bowler.
FOUR BYES! Misses everyone. Full length, down leg. Imam-ul-Haq fails to tickle it away. The swing beats the effort of Niroshan Dickwella behind the sticks and races away to the boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length, angled across the left-hander, in the channel. Imam-ul-Haq stays back and shoulders his arms at it.
A length ball, wide outside off, at 130 clicks. Imam-ul-Haq covers his stumps and lets it through to the keeper.
Fraction short, outside off. Azam punches it to cover.
This one comes in with the arm. Full, on middle. Azam strides forward to block it out.
Too short, outside off. Azam stays on his back foot and punches it to point, only to find the fielder.
Tossed up, outside off, pushed to the off side.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Azam blocks it out watchfully.
A maiden for Prabath Jayasuriya. His first one of the innings. Flighted, full and on off. Babar Azam gets on his front foot and blocks it off his inner half.
Asitha Fernando comes 'round the wicket now. It is a length ball, angled into the pads. Imam-ul-Haq stays back and flicks it to square leg.
Fuller this time, on fifth stump. Imam-ul-Haq defends it to the off side solidly.
The dot balls have started to creep up. Full length, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq gets behind the line and drives it gently back to the bowler.
Imam-ul-Haq is yet to get off the back. Asitha Fernando drags his length back, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq dabs it to backward point.
FOUR! Imam-ul-Haq is off the mark in fine fashion. Back of a length, wide outside off. Imam-ul-Haq stays back and cuts hard at it. It goes over point and into the boundary.
Length ball, on off, defended out watchfully. Only a boundary off the over. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Tossed up full on off, Babar Azam uses his feet and blocks it out.
Floated around middle, Babar Azam pushes this back to the bowler.
Flatter and quicket on middle and leg, Babar Azam knocks it to the leg side.
On off, kept out.
Pitched up on middle, Babar Azam comes down the track and drives it towards covers.
On off, blocked out on the front foot. A maiden to start the second session on Day 2.
FOUR! Great shot! This is full and on middle, angling in, Imam-ul-Haq smears it past the mid on fielder for a boundary.
On a length and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq knocks it to the leg side.
Good length on off, Imam-ul-Haq gets behind the line and blocks it off.
FOUR! Second boundary of this over for Imam. This is short and wide outside off, Imam-ul-Haq cuts it past point for a lovely boundary.
Full and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq drills it towards mid off, he wants the single but Babar is not interested and sends him back.
On a length and outside off, Imam leaves it alone.

FOUR! The boundaries are flowing now. This is darted on the pads, Babar Azam skips down the track and tries to whips it towards mid-wicket but gets a thick inside edge and the ball runs away towards the deep square leg fence.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated on leg, Babar Azam knocks it past short leg.
Slower through the air on middle and leg, Babar Azam looks to block it but gets hit on the pads. The Sri Lankans appeal for an LBW but the finger stays down.
On off, kept out.
Full and on middle, Babar Azam uses his feet and pushes this back to the bowler.
Mendis starts with a short delivery, outside off, Imam-ul-Haq cuts it to deep cover for one.
FOUR! SMASHED! This is short again and on middle, Babar Azam goes back and smashes it behind square and picks up a boundary.
Floated on middle and leg, Babar Azam nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
BEATEN! Mendis bowls this short again but this time on middle and close to the body of batter. Imam-ul-Haq goes for the cut but misses the ball completely.
Outside off, Imam-ul-Haq pushes it to the left of point for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Azam works it to the right of the bowler. Mendis dives to that side and gets a hand on it. It goes towards mid on but there is no single there.
Good length, on off, Imam-ul-Haq wrists it towards square leg for a run.
