This is drifted into middle and leg, Babar gets a big stride forward and nudges it past short leg.
On off, solidly defended off the front foot.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Prabath Jayasuriya, the bowler in form gets the big fish! Jayasuriya goes a bit wider of the crease and tries to curve it in from wide outside off. Babar Azam goes chasing after a full and wide one and pays the price. Babar looks to cover drive, away from the body and with no feet movement, doesn't get to the pitch of the ball. The ball takes the inside edge and goes on to rattle the stumps. A huge moment in the innings as Babar departs cheaply and Jayasuriya is ecstatic.
Howout: b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Quicker and flatter on middle, angling in a bit, Mohammad Rizwan goes for the block but gets an inside edge towards square leg. They cross.
Loopy full toss, on middle and leg, Imam-ul-Haq comes down the track and eases it to long on for a single.
Starts off the new spell with a good-length delivery, angling across the left-hander, Imam-ul-Haq lets it through to the keeper.
Digs in a short one over leg stump, Imam rides the bounce well and pulls it down to deep mid-wicket for one.

FOUR! Poor delivery and it is duly punished! Short ball but sits up nicely for the batter, Mohammad Rizwan swivels and plays a controlled pull shot, all along the ground and into the backward square leg fence.
Length this time, angling in from around off, Rizwan tucks it away through mid-wicket for a run.
Length again and on the pads, Imam neatly works it away to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Goes full and on the fifth stump line, this is left alone for the keeper to collect.
Flatter trajectory, on a nagging length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq goes on the back foot to keep it out.
Floats it up full and on middle, this is flicked straight towards short mid-wicket.
On off, this is looped up just a bit, Imam pushes it towards covers.
Flighted this time, full and on off, driven straight towards extra cover.
Slows it up a touch and drifts it onto middle and leg, Imam looks to nudge on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
End of another probing over by Jayasuriya. This is dropped a bit short and Imam-ul-Haq works it off the back foot through mid-wicket for a single.
This is pushed well wide of the off stump and Imam has nothing to do with it.
Delivered on a good length, around off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it from inside the crease.
Bowled a bit fuller and floated up on the pads, Imam-ul-Haq looks to work it leg side but gets squared up a bit and gets an outside edge towards the gully region.
On a hard length, over middle, Imam gets well behind the line of the ball and makes the block.

Excellent work in the deep! Banged in short and at a good height over middle, Imam-ul-Haq lays into it and pulls it hard towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder runs around from deep square leg and dives to his right to make the stop as the batters get back for two.
Pitches it up now, in the channel around off and Imam leaves it alone.
Nicely looped up, on off, Rizwan defends it off the front foot.
Floated up, full and on off, Mohammad Rizwan tries to make room and thrash it through covers but finds the man.
Sliding into middle and leg, flicked away towards square leg.
Around off, Rizwan keeps it out on the off side.
Gives it a bit more air and serves it on off stump, Rizwan does well to make the block.
Tossed up on middle, Rizwan skips down the track and drives it to mid on for a quick single.
Back of a length, on leg stump, this is tucked away off the hips towards mid-wicket for one.
Pitched up on middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
This is full and on leg stump, Imam flicks it in front of mid-wicket and races back for two.
Good length and excellent line as well, close to the off pole. Imam-ul-Haq makes a watchful leave.
Length again, on the pads this time and worked away to deep square leg for a single.
Pitched up around off, Rizwan punches it straight back to the bowler.
Floated and full, around off. Imam-ul-Haq comes down the track and blocks it into the deck.
Looped up, around off, blocked out solidly.
Flighted this, full and on off. Imam-ul-Haq remains solid in his defense.
Four dots in a row now. This is full, around off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it back to the bowler on the front foot.

MISFILED AND FOUR! It is tossed up, full and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq gets to the pitch of the delivery and drives it firmly to the right of mid off. Ramesh Mendis moves to that side but slide over the ball. The ball goes through and races away to the boundary. A well created shot by Imam-ul-Haq.
On off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it out watchfully. Pakistan trail by 332.
Darted on the pads, Rizwan stays back and tucks it to short leg.
Length ball, on off. Rizwan works it to mid on.
Slower through the air, on off. Rizwan defends it on the front foot.
Around off, turns in a touch. Mohammad Rizwan strides forward and clips it to the leg side.
Flatter and on off. Rizwan punches it to long on for an easy single.
A single of the last ball! It is outside off. Imam-ul-Haq guides it through backward point for another single. Only 2 runs off the over. A tidy one from the acting skipper.
Around off, defended out.
Slower one, full and on off. Imam-ul-Haq gets enough time to block it into the deck.
This is one is flighted on leg. Imam-ul-Haq comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is full and on off. Rizwan comes down the track and drills it past the mid on fielder. It races away. Mohammad Rizwan is seeing the ball big here.
On off, defended out.
Floated and full, around off. Rizwan blocks it out watchfully.
This one is on the pads, Imam-ul-Haq stays back and flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.

OUT! TIMBER! Dhananjaya de Silva strikes and finds the third wicket for his side. He will be surely happy to see the back of Imam-ul-Haq. Dhananjaya de Silva serves a loopy delivery, outside off, that comes in with the arm. Imam-ul-Haq tries to defend it out but plays the wrong line. The ball sneaks through the gap between bat and pad to rattle the furniture behind. Sri Lanka are dominating the proceeding here.
Howout: b Dhananjaya de Silva

Commentary: WOAH! This is close. It is looped up, around off. It turns away sharply off the deck with some extra bounce. Alam tries to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge. Niroshan Dickwella appeals louldly for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved. They do not take the review and rightly so as the replay shows that there was no edge on it.
On off, blocked out.
Fuller, on off. Alam pushes it to mid off for a single. He gets off the mark.
Full and on off. Rizwan gets behind and blocks it out. A wicket-taking over comes to an end.
Flighted and full, outside off. Alam gets on his front foot to block it away.
An arm ball now, around off. Alam stays back to block it.
It is quicker and on the pads, Alam flicks it to mid-wicket.
This is on the stumps. Alam stays back and blocks it into the deck.
Full length, outside off. Alam gets behind and defends it.
It is darted on the pads, Alam flicks it to mid-wicket, not in the gap though. Prabath Jayasuriya records his third maiden of the innings.
Tossed up on off, Mohammad Rizwan blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Mohammad Rizwan thinks about whipping it but at end pushes it back to the bowler.
Pushed through quicker, short and on leg, Mohammad Rizwan tucks it uppishly past short leg for a single.
Shortish and on middle, Fawad Alam defends it from his back foot.
Floated on middle, skids through, Fawad Alam knocks it to the leg side.
Darted on a yorker length, on middle, Fawad Alam digs it back to the bowler.
Short and on middle and leg, Mohammad Rizwan pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Floated on middle and leg, Mohammad Rizwan goes back and wrists it towards mid on for one.
Tossed up on middle, Fawad Alam tucks it to mid-wicket. The fielder does well to stop the ball.
Shortish again and on middle, Fawad Alam stays back and blocks it out.
Tossed up on middle, Fawad Alam nudges it to mid-wicket.
Floated outside off, Fawad Alam pads it away.
FOUR! Loose delivery by DDS. This tossed up full on middle, Mohammad Rizwan goes down and sweeps it fine towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary,
Floated on middle, Mohammad Rizwan drills it towards long off for a single.
Floats this from 'round the wicket, on off, Fawad Alam defends it well.
Flighted delivery and wide of off, Fawad Alam again is solid in his defense.
This is slower through the air on middle, Fawad Alam goes to block it but gets a leading edge back to the bowler.
FOUR! A boundary to end the over then. This is short and on middle, Fawad Alam pulls it hard in front of square for a boundary.
A bit short and on off, Mohammad Rizwan guides it with soft hands towards short third man.
Short and angled into the pads, Mohammad Rizwan stays back and works it through square leg for one.
Floated on off, spins in sharply, Fawad Alam blocks it out well.
Tossed up full on off, Fawad Alam drives this towards mid on and gets across for a quick single.
Darts this one on middle, Mohammad Rizwan uses his feet and pushes it towards mid on for another run. This is good strike rotation from the batters.
This is outside off. Alam cuts it through point for one.
Short and outside off, Fawad Alam stays back and cuts it with the spin towards point. There is a fumble and they get back for the second.
Floated on middle, Fawad Alam blocks it from his back foot.

Almost for Mendis. He bowls the arm ball on middle, skids onto the batter, Fawad Alam goes for the block but gets an inside edge and the ball goes through his legs and just past the stumps. Lucky escape for Alam.
Short and outside off, Fawad Alam stays back and punches it through covers for one.
Short and on off. Rizwan pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and on off. Alam comes down the track and flicks it to mid on. They cross for a single.
Flatter, around off. Fawad Alam flicks it to square leg for a single.
Slower through the air, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan slashes it to cover for a quick single.
Floated and full, on fourth stump. Alam blocks it out on his front foot.
Pushed through quicker, on off. Alam is solid in his defense.
Flighted, on off. Alam blocks it out watchfully.
Flatter, around off. Alam punches it to cover, not in the gap though.
This one lands outside off and turns in off the deck. It also hurries onto the batter. Rizwan goes back and does enough to keep it out.

OUT! It looks to be plumb! Ramesh Mendis appeals for lbw and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Mohammad Rizwan has a chat with his partner at the other end and goes for the review with just one second on the timer. Coming to the delivery. It is full and on leg. This stays low a touch off the deck. Mohammad Rizwan tries to block it out but misses. He gets rapped on his pads. The original decision is OUT. The review also does not help Rizwan, as the Ball Tracking shows three reds. Pakistan are in a spot of bother here.
Howout: lbw b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Drifts it in full and on leg stump, Agha Salman nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Cries of 'catch it,' but it's out of reach. This is turning into the pads, Salman looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball loops up and falls wide of short leg.
On a length and around middle, blocked out.
Beaten! This is full and outside off from Ramesh Mendis. Agha Salman looks to play for the turn which isn't there and gets beaten past the outside edge.
Quicker delivery, on leg stump, Fawad Alam manages to keep it out.
Quicker and flatter, once again on leg stump, Alam goes deep in his crease to defend it out.
Thinks about the single but decides against it. Full and on middle, Fawad Alam edges it with soft hands towards point.
On the shorter side and around off, this is punched off the back foot through covers for a single.
Tossed up on off, Salman blocks it off the front foot.
Nicely flighted, around off, Salman presses forward and drives it towards cover.
Flatter delivery, around off, Fawad Alam looks to play it onto the off side but edges it down through short third man for just a single.
Floated up, on off, Salman keeps it out.
Tosses it up outside off now, Salman stroke sit towards cover-point for a run.
Drops it short and outside off, Fawad Alam plays it off the back foot towards deep cover for one more.
On a length and turning in a long way from middle and leg, Salman keeps it down past short leg.
Slower through the air and around off, Salman leans in and blocks it out.
This is darted onto middle, Alam flicks it towards mid-wicket.
On the pads, nudged away toward short leg.
Loopy delivery, on middle and leg, Alam manages to keep it out.
Just a tad shorter and on off, Fawad Alam backs away and eases it through extra cover for a single.

Nicely bowled! This is sliding into the pads, Agha Salman looks to defend off the front foot but gets an inside edge through leg slip. The batters come back for two as the short fine leg fielder chases it down and keeps it out.
Flighted, around middle and leg, blocked out.
Nicely bowled! On a nagging length and turning away from middle, Fawad Alam does well to get behind the line and make the block.
Unplayable! A nice bit of drift into the off stump of the left-hander and the ball just turns enough to beat the defense of Fawad Alam.
On a length and around off, Alam goes back and across to defend.
On off, blocked out solidly.
Floated and full, outside off. Alam remains solid in his defense.
Fuller, outside off. Alam strides forward to block it out. A great over by Mendis comes to an end.
This one is angled in, around off. Salman blocks it to covers.
Fuller and on off. Salman gets down the track and plays it back to the bowler. Prabath Jayasuriya gets a hand on it and kills the pace of the ball.
Floated, on the pads, Agha Salman flicks it to mid on for a single. Good running here. They trail by 282 runs.
Quicker, full and on off. Alam defends it with straight bat.
Looped up, around middle and leg. Alam nudges it to the leg side.
Three dots in a row to end the over. This is full, on the pads, Alam stays back and clips it to square on the leg side.
Fuller, outside off. Salman defends it to cover on the front foot.
Flighted and full, outside off. Salman strokes it to sweeper cover and collects a brace.
Fuller, around off. Salman works it back to the bowler off the outer half as he tries to tuck this to the leg side.
On leg, flicked to mid-wicket.
Length ball, on off. Salman eases it back to the bowler.
Agha Salman defends this full delivery on the front foot.
Dunith Wellalage serves it short and on leg first up. Alam pulls it to deep square leg and crosses for a single.
Nice fielding in the deep! It is tossed up, on leg. Salman gets low and sweeps it down to fine leg. Asitha Fernando sprints to his right from deep square leg and keeps it down to three.
On off, blocked out.
A single now as this is flicked to square leg.
Fuller, around off. Salman pushes it past point for a brace. This is good running.
Pushed through quicker, on off. Salman defends it to cover on the front foot and scampers across for a quick single. 8 runs come off the over then.
Flighted and full, on off. Salman defends it out solidly.

FOUR BYES! Misses everyone! It is sprayed down leg. The ball bounces a bit more off the deck. It goes past Niroshan Dickwella and races away. The ball goes down to the fine leg fence. The umpire signals byes.
On off, pushed to point, not in the gap though.
Full and on off. Salman strides forward and blocks it out.
Tossed up, around middle. Salman remains solid in his defense.
Flatter, on the pads, Salman flicks it to square leg for one.
Fraction shorter, around off. Salman stays back and punches it to cover.
Agha Salman gets forward and defends this full delivery into the deck.
Slower through the air, around off. Salman drives it towards mid off.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
Tossed up, around off, turns in a touch. Salman works it to covers.
Dunith Wellalage records his first maiden of the innings. It is full and on off. Salman gets forward to block it out. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2.
Starts from around the wicket and drifts it full on the pads, Fawad Alam manages to keep it out on the leg side.
First runs of the session! On the shorter side and around off, Alam eases it through covers for a single.
Flighted, around off and drawing the batter forward, Salman edges it down with soft hands towards gully.
Tossed up on off, Agha Salman with a nice cover drive but straight to the fielder at extra cover.
On middle and leg, this is turned towards mid-wicket.
On a good length and around off, Salman taps it towards short cover.
Starts the new spell from around the wicket and pitches it up around off stump. Fawad Alam leans forward and pushes it out.
This is a tad fuller and angling into middle, Alam gets across to cover the line well and blocks it out.
Good length, around off stump, Alam taps it towards short cover.
Digs in a bouncer now, over off stump and at a good height too. Fawad Alam ducks under it with ease though.
Length this time, angling onto the pads, this is worked away behind square on the leg side for a single.
Just a hint of reverse swing there! On a nagging length, around off and just tails back in a touch. Agha Salman gets it off the inner half of the bat and towards backward square leg. Single taken.
On middle and leg, nudged away onto the leg side.
Turning onto the pads, Salman dabs it past short leg and picks up a single.
Excellent running! On off and turning away from the left-hander, Alam waits for it and taps it towards point for a quick single.
Shortens the length and turns it in from around off, Salman goes on the back foot and tickles it towards short fine leg.
Flatter delivery, around middle and this is kept out off the back foot.
Tosses it up, full and on off, Salman strides forward to make the block.
Around the wicket now for the left-hander. This is on the shorter side and around the fifth stump line, Fawad Alam hangs back and steers it towards short third man.
Just a hint of shape away from the left-hander, this is floated up around off and shaping away. Alam pushes at it gently and gets it past the man at extra cover for a couple of runs.
Length, angling in from around off. On this occasion, Fawad Alam is a bit late but luckily for him not too late as he manages to keep it out.
Goes full and on off, this is pushed back towards the bowler.

Living a bit dangerously here Fawad Alam! Banged in halfway down the track and the ball is around the helmet height. Alam is a bit late on the hook shot and plays it uppishly towards the vacant mid-wicket region. Picks up a single as well.
Good length, on middle and leg, kept out on the leg side.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb! Ramesh Mendis picks up his second wicket of the innings and sends back a dangerous man in Fawad Alam. This could well be the opening that the Sri Lankans were after. It is tossed up, around middle and leg. Alam comes across and tries to block it out but misses. He gets rapped on the pads and Mendis turns around to make a loud appeal. The umpire agrees and raises his dreaded finger and Alam doesn't even review it, rightly so.
Howout: lbw b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: On off, blocked out.
This is angled into middle. Nawaz blocks it to cover on the front foot.
Touch shorter, outside off. Nawaz dabs it to backward point.
This is floated, outside off, straightens a bit off the deck. Nawaz watches it sail past him.
Close! This is flighted and full, around middle. Nawaz gets his blade down in time to block it away. A wicket-maiden for Mendis this time. Sri Lanka on the driving seat here.
Too short, on off. Salman stays back and pushes it to backward point. They take two.
Asitha Fernando hits the hard length this time, around off. Salman sways away from the line of the delivery.
Length ball, on off, blocked out watchfully.
Full length, on the pads, Salman flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Mohammad Nawaz gets off the mark with a boundary. It is full and outside off. Nawaz leans in and creams it through covers for a cracking boundary. They trail by 252 runs now.
Asitha Fernando fires it into the pads. Nawaz stays back and flicks it through square leg for one.
Fuller, on off, Nawaz blocks it out watchfully.
Looped up, full and on off. Nawaz blocks it out solidly.
Fuller, on off. Nawaz smothers it to cover.
Floated and full, outside off. Nawaz drives it uppishly through covers. It is in the gap and they take one.
On the stumps. Salman blocks it out to covers.
Flighted and full, outside off. Salman goes for the drive but only as far as the cover fielder.
Asitha Fernando serves a short ball, on middle. Mohammad Nawaz ducks under it without any hesitation.
Back of a length now, down leg. Nawaz lets it be.
A bouncer again, on middle. Nawaz ducks under it wisely.
Another short one, outside off. Nawaz leaves it alone.
Full length, on off. Nawaz drives it down the ground. Prabath Jayasuriya gives it a chase and saves a certain boundary. The batters take three.
Length ball, outside off. Salman punches it to cover. Ramesh Mendis makes a superb stop with a dive. Just three runs off the over then.
Tossed up, fuller, outside off. Nawaz drives it to cover but straight to the fielder.
Outside off. Nawaz drives it to cover on the up. Jeffrey Vandersay dives to his left to make a stop.
Length ball, on off. Nawaz punches it to the right of cover. Jeffrey Vandersay moves to that side and makes another good stop.
It is tossed up, around middle. It stays low off the deck. Nawaz stays back and gets his blade down in time.
Outside off, left alone.
Floated and full, on off. Nawaz blocks it out solidly. Mendis records his fourth maiden of the innings.
Prabath Jayasuriya starts with a juicy full toss on off, Agha Salman only manages to push this back to the bowler.
Another full toss on leg this time, Agha Salman flicks it but finds the short leg fielder. He will be dissapointed to miss out on that.
Tossed up on off, Agha Salman knocks it to covers.
Flatter delivery on off, Agha Salman leans on and blocks it out.
On middle, blocked out.
A maiden over by Prabath Jayasuriya. This is tossed up on middle and off, Agha Salman defends to the off side.
Floated on off, Mohammad Rizwan knocks it towards short mid off.
Flighted delivery on middle, turning away a bit, Mohammad Nawaz goes for the block but gets an outside edge towards point.
Full and on off, Mohammad Nawaz is solid in his defense.
Darts this one full, angling into the pads, Mohammad Nawaz clips it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Agha Salman leans on to defend and plays it towards short leg with the inner half of his willow.
Floated on middle, Agha Salman blocks it out well.
Tossed up on off, Mohammad Nawaz pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery around off, Mohammad Nawaz works it straight to short covers.
Flatter and a bit quicker on middle and leg, Mohammad Nawaz tucks it away to short mid-wicket.
Almost on a yorker length, Mohammad Nawaz digs it back to the bowler.
On off, kept out.
Another maiden by Prabath Jayasuriya. This is floated on off, Mohammad Nawaz blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on off, Agha Salman defends it onto the pitch. He is not able to rotate the strike.
This pushed through quicker on off, Agha Salman goes for the reverse sweep but could not connect. Niroshan Dickwella does well to stop the ball.

Slower through the air on middle, turning in sharply, Agha Salman goes for the block but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Probably the turn saved Salman.
On off, kept out.
Short and outside off, Agha Salman pushes it past point for a single.
Short again and outside off, Mohammad Nawaz punches it towards deep cover for one.
Flighted on off, Mohammad Nawaz guides it towards point for one.

SIX! Huge hit! This is tossed up on off, Agha Salman dances down the track and lofts it above the bowler's head and over the long off fence for a biggie. This is the first six for Agha Salman in Test cricket.
FOUR! Agha Salman finding the boundaries now. This is floated on middle, Agha Salman picks the length early and goes down to sweep it fine towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Shorter in length and on off, Agha Salman knocks it to the off side.
Floated and full, on middle and leg, Agha Salman works it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up full and on off, Agha Salman leans on and defends it to the off side.
Beaten! This is on a length and around off, turns away sharply. Mohammad Nawaz looks to play it off the back foot but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Around off, blocked out onto the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A sharp catch by Niroshan Dickwella behind the sticks and Ramesh Mendis has his third! This is bowled on a nagging length and close to the off pole. There is a bit of turn on offer but once again Mohammad Nawaz looks to cut off the back foot rather than coming forward and this time he pays the price. The ball isn't short enough to cut and is too close to the stumps as well. Nawaz gets a thick outside edge that goes straight into the keeper's mitts. Sri Lanka well and truly in command here.
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Nicely flighted, around off. Yasir Shah gets a big stride forward and blocks it out.
Darts it into middle and leg, well defended off the front foot by Shah again.

A wicket-maiden! Looped up around off and turning in sharply, Yasir Shah manages to get his bat behind the line of the ball. This has been an excellent prolonged spell by Ramesh Mendis so far and he is showing no signs of fatigue either.
Risky from Agha Salman! Very full and on the stumps, Salman strides forward and just about manages to sweep it away behind square on the leg side for a single.
Nicely tossed up, around off and this is driven firmly towards extra cover.
Well flighted, gets it full and on off, Shah manages to block it out.
Slower through the air and on a length, around middle and leg, nudged away onto the leg side.
Flighted once again and around off, Shah stays solid in defense.
Gives it a bit more air this time and bowls it close to the off pole. Yasir Shah watchfully keeps it out towards point.
Loopy delivery, turning in sharply from around off, Salman gets well forward and keeps it out.
Shorter and turning into middle, Agha Salman looks to sweep but gets a top edge through leg slip and towards fine leg for a couple of runs.
Around off, kept out on the off side.

FOUR! Good stroke! Flighted, well outside off and turning in. Agha Salman uses his feet well to get to the pitch of the ball and lofts it towards the extra cover fence. With that, the 150 comes up for Pakistan.
Around middle, blocked out.
Floated up around off, Salman defends it off the front foot.
Holds it back a touch and curves it in from outside off, Shah keeps it out.
Looks to drift it onto the pads but serves a leg-stump half-volley, Yasir Shah strokes it away through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Darted into middle, Shah strides out to defend.
Around off, this is pushed towards extra cover.
A change-up now! Prabath Jayasuriya with a low round-arm action serves a quicker delivery on middle and leg. Yasir Shah does well to keep it out.
Now this one goes on with the arm! Flatter and on middle, sliding onto the pads. Yasir Shah looks to pad it away, the ball flicks the flap of the pad and goes straight into the pouches of leg slip.
On middle, defended off the front foot.
FOUR! Classical cover drive from Agha Salman and he is showing his worth here. Looped up, way too full and wide, Salman caresses it through covers for a boundary and moves into the 40s.
Mendis changes the line of attack and comes from around the attack. This is full and on leg stump, Salman keeps it out on the leg side.
Quicker and flatter, sliding across middle, Salman just about manages to get some bat on it.
On leg stump and turning into the pads, this is nudged away towards mid-wicket.
Floats it up across the off pole, Agha Salman strokes it away towards cover.
Full and on the stumps. Shah stays back and blocks it watchfully.
Prabath Jayasuriya serves it on middle and leg. Shah gets forward to defend.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Shah flicks it to mid-wicket but straight to the fielder.
Angles it in around off. Shah defends it out watchfully.
Darted on the pads, clipped to the leg side.
BEATEN! It is looped up, around off. It turns away with some extra bounce off the deck. Yasir Shah tries to poke at it but misses.
Fuller, on off. Salman sweeps it through square leg for a single.
A loopy full toss, on the pads, Shah clips it to the leg side for one more.
EDGY! It is floated and full, around off. Salman looks to flick it away to the leg side but it goes down to third man off the leading edge. They collect a brace.
On off, driven to mid on.
On the pads, Salman gets on the front foot and defends it to square leg. There is no one there and they scamper across for one. He moves to 44.
On off, blocked out watchfully.

FOUR! Fortunate boundary for Agha Salman. It is tossed up, outside off. Salman tries to drive it away. It takes a big outside edge and sneaks through the gap between the slip and the wicket-keeper. It races away to the boundary.
A single as this is pushed to covers.
Prabath Jayasuriya drags it down this time. Shah pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Floated and full, on off. Salman eases it back to the bowler.

Agha Salman has his maiden Test half-century. It is full and on off. Salman gets it to the leg side off the inner half. They take one. Everyone in the dressing room is up on their feet. This has been an incredible knock from Salman. Can he convert it into a three-digit score?
Around off, defended out solidly.
Drifts into the pads, Salman blocks it out solidly.
Around off, defended on the front foot.
Looped up, on leg. Salman sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Flighted and full, on off. Shah defends it to point.
It is looped up, around middle. Shah gets behind the line and makes the block.
Back of a length, outside off. Shah goes back and cuts it hard to point, only to find the fielder.
On off, blocked back to he bowler.
Length ball, on the stumps. Salman defends it back.
Floated and full, on fourth stump. Agha Salman gets on the front foot to block it out.
On off, Salman gets forward to defend it.
Darted on the pads, Salman clips it through square leg for one.
Full, on off. Shah gets it to point with an angled bat.
Pushed through quicker on middle and off, Agha Salman guides it with the outer half of his blade towards point.
Flatter and on middle and leg, Agha Salman goes to block but inside edges it through square leg for one.
Tossed up on middle, Yasir Shah uses his feet to get to the pitch of the ball and knocks it back to the bowler.
Floated and full, on middle, Yasir Shah once again pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle and leg, Yasir Shah blocks it out.
Slower through the air and around off, turning away a bit, Yasir Shah lets it go to the keeper.
Floated on middle and leg, Agha Salman knocks it towards short mid off.
Tossed up on middle and leg again, Agha Salman defends it to short mid-wicket.
Gives it some air this time, outside off, Agha Salman pushes it through covers for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Yasir Shah blocks it down the pitch.
This is floated around off, Yasir Shah strides forward and defends it towards silly point.
On middle, blocked out down the pitch.
Tossed up full and on middle, Agha Salman just drives it with full face of his bat towards long off for a single.
Floated on middle and leg, Yasir Shah tucks it away to mid on and get across for a quick single.
Full and on middle again, Agha Salman eases it to long off for one.
Flights this one up on leg, Yasir Shah pushes it towards silly mid on.
Tossed up again on off, Yasir Shah drives it firmly but straight to short covers.
Floats it up on off, Yasir Shah knocks it to short extra cover. He has been solid in his defense till now and supporting Agha Salman well.
Asitha Fernando starts with a full delivery and on outside off, Agha Salman opens the face of his bat and guides it past point for a brace. With that, the follow on has been avoided by Pakistan.
Full once again on middle, angling in, Agha Salman flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Serves it on a length and on off. Agha Salman strides forward and pushes it to short covers.

An appeal for caught behind but turned down. This full and down the leg, angling in, Agha Salman moves across to flick it but misses and gets hit on his pads. The ball goes straight into the keeper's gloves and they appeal for catch but the fingers stays down. Sri Lanks do not opt for the review.
In the blockhole, on middle, Agha Salman manages to dig it out.
On a length and on off, Agha Salman drives it straight to short covers.
A low full toss on middle, Yasir Shah looks to flick it away but finds the hands of short leg fielder.
Tossed up on middle, Yasir Shah blocks it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle and leg, Yasir Shah leans on and knocks it towards short mid on.
Flatter and on leg, angling in, Yasir Shah defend it with the inner half to the leg side.
Almost on a yorker length, Yasir Shah uses his feet and digs it out down the pitch.
This is slower through the air, turning away a bit, Yasir Shah goes back and tucks it down towards short leg.
Length ball, tailing in a bit into off and this is clipped away towards deep vackward square leg for a single.
This is dug in short and over middle, Yasir Shah hops and plays it with soft hands down on the leg side.
Shorter length and around off, Shah looks for the cracking pull shot but mistimes it badly towards mid-wicket.
Goes full and straight now, with a hint of reverse, this is flicked away straight to mid-wicket.
Banged in short again and around off, Shah does well to keep it down on the leg side. Asitha Fernando mixing up his lengths well at the moment.

Just short! Asitha Fernando switches to around the wicket and digs it short and on the bodyline, Yasir Shah gets himself strangled as he looks to fend it away. The ball goes off the top edge and loops up around leg slip. Dhananjaya de Silva is a bit too deep at leg gully and can't get to the ball. He puts in a late dive forward but the ball lands safely and hits him on his cheek. This should wake him up. A chance goes begging for Sri Lanka there.
Full and around off, driven down to long off for a single.
Floated up on middle and leg, Shah pushes it back to the bowler.
Nicely flighted, on off and Yasir Shah defends it off the front foot.
Slows it up a touch and drifts it onto middle and leg, Shah strides forward to defend.
Switches to over the wicket now and slides it across the right-hander, Shah pushes it out on the off side.
Shorter and angling well across the off stump, Yasir Shah has enough time to rock back and punch it towards sweeper cover for one.
Short and on leg stump, Shah with a look-away flick down to fine leg for a single, nonchalantly done.
Keeps bowling it short and down the leg side this time, a bit slower as well. Agha Salman ducks under it with ease.
Short again! Banged in over middle and leg and Salman has no intentions of playing at that one as he ducks under it once again.

The previous two deliveries were the set up for this delivery but Fernando can't quite execute it properly. Goes full and straight, and looks for the reverse-swinging yorker that ends up being a low full toss on middle. Agha Salman works it in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Another short ball, around leg stump and Shah ducks under it.
Ends up with another short ball but this time it is angled across the off stump. Yasir Shah hops and keeps it down towards short leg.
Floats it up around middle and leg, Salman works it towards mid-wicket.
A bit quicker and turning down leg, left alone.
On the shorter side, on the pads, Salman goes on the back foot and turns it through mid-wicket for an easy single. This partnership really frustrating the Lankan bowlers at the moment.

SIX! BANG! Ramesh Mendis is back to over the wicket and Yasir Shah immediately goes on the attack. This is tossed up around off and turning in, Shah dances down the track and powers it flush into the boundary cushion at the long on fence. The third umpire has a couple of looks at it and deems that it is a maximum.

This is tossed up, full and around middle and leg, turning in sharply. Yasir Shah looks to defend off the back foot but gets pinged on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW and it is given! Yasir Shah though reviews it almost immediately. The third umpire checks UltraEdge and finds that there's no bat involved. Ball Tracking though shows that the ball was turning and would have missed the leg stump. Brilliant review from Shah and his stay at the crease will continue.
On middle and leg, kept out on the leg side.
Flatter, around leg stump, just tickled 'round the corner.
Flights it up on a length from around the stumps and, Agha Salman leaves it on line.
On off, Salman defends it off the front foot.

OUT! TAKEN! Dhananjaya de Silva makes amends for some lazy work earlier and takes a sharp catch. Nicely tossed up by Prabath Jayasuriya, on a nagging length and on off stump. There is a bit of drift into the right-hander and then the ball just grips and turns away, a dream delivery for a slow left-armer. Agha Salman puts a big stride forward to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and de Silva takes a very good catch to his left at first slip. Salman has to walk back in disappointment as he fails to see out Day 2 but Sri Lanka have the breakthough they so desperately wanted.
Howout: c Dhananjaya de Silva b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Starts off with a floated delivery, around off. Hasan Ali puts a big stride forwaard to defend.
Nicely flighted, on middle, blocked off by Ali.
On the money first ball. Perfect length, on off and this is defended off the front foot by Yasir Shah.
Goes full and straight, Yasir Shah whips it well in front of square on the leg side and picks up a couple of runs, the first runs of the day as well.
Thinking about the second but Hasan Ali sends his partner back. Good length, over middle, Shah dabs it down towards backward square leg for a single.
Just a hint of reverse there. On a fullish length and tailing in late into middle, Ali solidly keeps it out.
Goes shorter this time and keeps it around the off pole, Ali lets it through to the keeper.
A single to end the over and Hasan Ali is off the mark. Back of a length, on off, Ali punches it off the back foot towards deep point for one.
Flighted, full and outside off, Ali shoulders arms to it.
Loopy delivery, drifted onto middle, Ali strides out to make the block.
On a length and considerably slowed up, around off, Ali taps it towards point.
On a nagging length, around off and turning away a touch, Ali keeps it out off the back foot.
Nicely bowled! Drifted onto middle and leg, holding it back a touch, Ali makes a good front-foot block.
Maiden! Tossed up full and on middle, Hasan Ali pushes it firmly back towards the bowler who makes a half stop.
Length ball, at a gentle pace and spilled down leg, left alone by Shah.
Length again, just tailing it in from around off and hunting that front pad. Well blocked by Yasir Shah.
Short of a good length, over off, Shah with a stylish dab towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fullish delivery, shaping in from outside off, solidly blocked out by Ali.
This is dug in a bit short and on the fourth stump line, Hasan Ali just sways away from the line of the ball to leave it for the keeper to collect.

Good aggression from Asitha Fernando but well played by Hasan Ali as well. Switches to around the wicket for the last delivery and angles a spicy short ball across the middle stump, Ali bends his back and manages to get away from the line of the ball.
On off, kept out on the off side by Shah.
Drifts it onto the pads, Yasir Shah keeps it down towards short leg.
This is darted onto middle and leg, Shah plays it with soft hands well in front of short leg.
Pushed through on middle, Shah pushes it to the eight of the bowler.
And again! Nagging length, around middle and leg, defended off the front foot.

BEATEN! Flights it up around the off pole and gets the ball to drift in and then turn away sharply. Yasir Shah looks to defend but gets beaten past the outside edge. Another maiden for Prabath Jayasuriya.
Good length but way down the leg side and no need to play at that one.
This is banged in short and over leg stump, Ali sways away from the line of the ball.
Short again and around leg stump, this time Ali ducks under it.
Back to over the wicket now, shorter in length and around off, this is punched out towards covers.
Shorter and angling down leg, Hasan Ali works it off his hips towards leg gully.
Back of a length and over off, this is defended off the back foot.
Tossed up full on middle, Yasir Shah knocks it to short leg.
Flighted on middle and leg, Yasir Shah defends it with the inner half to the leg side.
On middle, blocked out by Shah.
Another flighted delivery on middle, Yasir Shah strides forward and blocks it with the inner half to short leg.
Pushed through a bit quicker and on leg, Yasir Shah flicks it through square leg for one.
SIX! Massive hit from Ali. This is tossed up on off, Hasan Ali dances down the track and heaves it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie. With that shot, the 200 comes up for Pakistan.
Ramesh Mendis starts with a short ball and on middle and leg, Yasir Shah tucks it towards deep square leg for one.
Sharp turn! This is slower through the air and around off, turning in sharply, Hasan Ali is caught in his crease and gets hit on the pads. There is a slight appeal for LBW but the finger stays down.
Shortish and on middle and leg, Hasan Ali works it through square leg and picks up two. Good running between the wickets by the batters.
On off, kept out.
Flatter and quicker on middle, Hasan Ali blocks it to mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, Hasan Ali pushes it to short leg.
Tossed up on middle, Yasir Shah leans on and blocks it out.
On middle, blocked out.
Gives it some air this time and on middle, turning away a bit, Yasir Shah gets a thick outside edge towards point.
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up full on off, Yasir Shah makes room and drives it past covers for one.
Pushed through quicker on middle, Hasan Ali pushes it towrds mid off.
Tossed up on middle, Yasir Shah uses his feet to heave it over mid-wicket but mistimes his shot towards square leg. They cross.
Floated on middle, Hasan Ali comes forward to block it but gets hit on the thigh pad due to the extra bounce.
Quicker delivery and a bit short on middle, Hasan Ali knocks it to short leg.
Short and outside off, Hasan Ali defends it of the back foot.
Sliding onto the pads, Ali tickles it down to fine leg for a single.
Fuller and around off, Shah prods and defends it out.
Floated on middle, Hasan Ali makes room to cut it but only manages to knock it back to the bowler.
Tossed up full on off, Hasan Ali blocks it out well.
On off, kept out.
Slightly quicker and on off again, Hasan Ali leans on and defends it to onto the pitch.
Shortish and outside off, Hasan Ali punches it of the back foot through covers for one.
Tossed up full and outside off, Yasir Shah pushes it toward silly point.
Starts off with a fullish ball on off, Hasan Ali has a big swing across the line but gets nowhere near the ball. Luckily for Ali, the ball goes over the off stump.
This is short and down leg, Ali leaves it alone.
On a good length and over off, this is eased away through covers for a single.
Leg bye! On the shorter side and down leg, Yasir Shah looks to work it off his hips but misses. The ball goes off the pads towards backward square leg and the batters get a leg bye.
Nicely bowled! just holds it back a touch and serves a full delivery outside off, Ali looks to drive but doesn't use his feet and misses.
Length, around off, this is pushed through covers for one.
This is curving in from outside off, Ali solidly keeps it out.

Prabath Jayasuriya slides one into the pads, Hasan Ali looks to defend off the front foot but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Huge appeal for LBW but it is not given. Dhananjaya de Silva opts for the review almost immediately. The third umpire checks for UltraEdge and finds that there's no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows that the impact is in line but the ball is just clipping leg stump and hence, wickets are umpire's call. Ali survives.
Around off, kept out on the off side by Ali.
Tossed up around off, this is stroked away through extra cover for a single.
Firmly struck! Full and on the stumps, Yasir Shah steps out and punches it to the left of the fielder at mid on. The fielder does get a hand to it as the batters get a couple of runs.
On a length, sliding into middle and leg, Shah looks to play it with soft hands but gets an inside edge past short leg.

Now that's some delivery! This is banged in short and with some heat behind it. The line is perfect too, angling into the left shoulder of Hasan Ali who does extremely well to get out of the way of the ball, falling over in the process.
Shorter and down leg, this is whipped away off the hips towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs.
Two more! Loose from Asitha Fernando, short and wide, Ali thrashes it through the point region and picks up another brace.
Back of a length, around off, this is punched off the back foot towards mid off.

Leading edge but falls safely! Just short of a length, angling in from around off. Hasan Ali looks to work it leg side but gets a leading edge that loops up and goes towards the vacant backward point region. A single is taken.
Length, around the top of off, Yasir Shah looks to drop nad run but the fielder at cover-point is quick to attack the ball.
Holds it back a touch and serves it on off stump, Ali watchfully keeps it out on the off side.
Darted in on the pads, Hasan Ali flicks it in front of mid-wicket and picks up a couple of runs.
On a length, around leg stump, Ali dabs it down with soft hands past short leg.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Finally, Prabath Jayasuriya does get the breakthrough! Floats it up full and around off stump, Hasan Ali gets down on one knee and looks for the big slog-sweep against the turn. Ali ends up getting a faint inside edge and the ball goes on to hit the base of the stumps. Ali walks back in utter disappointment after playing a decent hand but the man who can do nothing wrong at the moment, Prabath Jayasuriya gives Sri Lanka the opening they were looking for and Pakistan now trail by 155 runs.
Howout: b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: There is an appeal from the Lankans for LBW but it is turned down. This is floated up, around off stump and turning in. Nauman Ali looks to defend it out but misses and the ball clips the back leg. It seems to be too high and there is no review.
Around off, blocked out by Ali.
Dug in halfway down the pitch and over middle, Yasir Shah pulls it behind square on the leg side for a single.
A bumper, over leg stump, Nauman Ali ducks under it with ease.
The bowler seems interested but no one else supports him. Goes full this time, on off, Nauman Ali gets a big inside edge back onto the pads.
Well bowled and equally well played. This is very full and on off, with a hint of shape away as well. Ali digs it out back towards the bowler.
This is the cross-seamer, banged in short and around leg. The ball doesn't rise up much but Ali manages to duck under it.
Switches to around the wicket for the final delivery and angles it down the leg side, Ali misses the flick as the keeper collects the ball.
On off, defended to covers.
Floated and full, on leg stump. Shah dances down the track and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Prabath Jayasuriya continues to ask the right questions. It is tossed up, around off, turning away. Ali strides forward to defend it out but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes to the right of the second slip fielder, Kusal Mendis, who make a full stretched dive to his left but only gets fingertips on it.
On off, defended out.
Ali pushes this full delivery to cover for a single.
Fuller, on off, Shah blocks it out watchfully.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ramesh Mendis is brought into the attack and strikes instantly. This one drifts in, lands on off, and turns away off the deck. Ali presses forward to block it out but misses. It takes the outside edge and Niroshan Dickwella makes no mistake behind the sticks.
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Angled into the pads, Naseem stays back and blocks it out.
Fuller, on middle, this one stays low. Naseem Shah gets his blade down in time.
This is pushed through quicker, on the pads, Shah stays back and blocks.
Fuller, outside off. Naseem gets it to backward point off the outer half. Yasir looks for a single but is sent back.
Ramesh Mendis starts his spell on Day 3 with a wicket maiden. It is full, around leg. Naseem blocks it to short leg.
Almost on a yorker length, on middle, Yasir Shah digs it towards long on for a single.
Floated on middle and off, Naseem Shah knocks it back to the bowler.

Darts this one on off, angling in with the arm, Naseem Shah goes on his back foot to block it but gets a little late and knocks it onto his pads. There is an appeal for LBW as the fielders think it is pad first, but the finger stays down. DDS takes the review at the last moment. The replay clearly shows that Naseem has hit this with the bat and UltraEdge confirms it. Sri Lanka lose their review.
FOUR! Anywhere will do at the moment for Naseem Shah. Tossed up on leg stump, Shah dances down the track and throws his hands at it, gets a faint inside edge that runs away into the fine leg fence.
Around off, stroked away towards cover.
Angling into middle, this is knocked down to long on but Yasir Shah at the non-striker's end denies the single.

OUT! LBW! That is it for the Pakistan innings. Ramesh Mendis gets his fifth wicket and he is delighted. He floats this up on middle, drifting in a bit, Yasir Shah leans on to defend but plays down the wrong line completely and gets wrapped around the pads. There is an appeal for LBW and the finger goes up this time. Yasir Shah opts for the review immediately. The UltraEdge shows that there is no bat involved and Ball tracking shows that the ball is clipping the leg-stump and it is umpire's call on wicket. Yasir Shah's resistance comes to an end and with that, Pakistan end their innings on 231.
Howout: lbw b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Hasan Ali starts with a full-length delivery, angled across around off. Niroshan Dickwella taps it out to safety.
A length ball, on the off stump. Niroshan Dickwella gets across and gets it to square leg off the inisde edge. The batters run hard and get two. Niroshan Dickwella and Sri Lanka are off the mark.
FOUR! Easy pckings for Niroshan Dickwella. Ali sprays it down the leg side. Niroshan Dickwella stays back and tickles it down to fine leg for a boundary.
Yet again Ali strays down the leg side. Niroshan Dickwella flicks it to deep square leg and gets a couple more.
Hasan Ali fires in a yorker this time, on off. Niroshan Dickwella jams it out solidly.
Full length, outside off, shaping away. Niroshan Dickwella has no shot to offer. Sri Lanka are off to a flying start with 8 runs off the first over, thanks to Dickwellla.
TWO LEG BYES! Good length, on the pads, Fernando tries to clip it but misses. It goes down to fine leg off his pads. They collect two leg byes.
Good length, outside off. Oshada Fernando goes for the drive on the off side, but gets it to square leg off the inside edge. They take two.
Shorter one, outside off, shaping away. Oshada Fernando leaves it alone.
This one is straightens off the deck, on a good length and in the channel. Oshada Fernando shuffles across and lets it through.
Back of a length, outside off. Fernando has no shot to offer.

BEATEN! Naseem Shah ends the over with a jaffa. Shah serves it on a length, in the channel of uncertainty, shaping away a bit. Fernando looks to defend it out but does so inside the line. The ball zips past the outside edge. Mohammad Rizwan and Naseem Shah make a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Length, on off, defended out.
Good length, angled across around off. Niroshan Dickwella stays back to block it out.
This one is outside off, shaping away. Niroshan Dickwella lets it through to the keeper.
Ali sprays this one down the leg side. Niroshan Dickwella does not chase it and Mohammad Rizwan gathers it with ease in his mitts.
Ali comes 'round the wicket. He serves a length ball, angled into the pads. Niroshan Dickwella flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Full length, on the pads. Fernando clips it to deep square leg for two runs. These two are making sure to keep the runs ticking.

This one does not carry! It is a length ball, angled across the left-hander. This one stays low off the deck. Niroshan Dickwella hangs his blade away from his body without any feet movement. He gets beaten on the inside edge.

Beaten again! It is touch fuller, outside off. Niroshan Dickwella gets on his front foot and tries to cream it through covers. He is a bit early into his shot and misses. The ball zips past the inside edge.
Length ball, around off, much closer to the body. Niroshan Dickwella stays back and blocks it watchfully.
Naseem Shah steams in and bends his back hard. It is a short ball, around leg. Niroshan Dickwella does well to sway away from the line.
Full length, on off. Niroshan Dickwella blocks it out with full face of the blade.
Full length, around middle and leg. Niroshan Dickwella flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
This is full, angled into the pads, Dickwella stay back and nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Hasan Ali errs in line this time and Fernando makes the most of it. It is full, angled down leg. Fernando stays back and flicks it through square on leg side. It races away to the boundary.
WIDE! It is full, wide outside off, shaping away sharply. It is way outside off and the umpire signals a wide.
Good length, outside off, no swing this time. Fernando shuffles across and leaves it alone.
Ali dishes a length ball, wide outside off, moving away. Fernando lets it be.

There is appeal for caught behind. The umpire shows no interest. Although there is some noise and Babar Azam decides to take the review here. Coming to the delivery, it is a full-length delivery, on fourth stump. Fernando goes for the drive but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge. There is some sound, maybe it is the bat hitting the deck, but Azam takes a review. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved and it is indeed the bat hitting the deck. Pakistan lose a review here.
Outside off, left alone. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Starts off the afternoon session with a good-length ball around the top of off, Niroshan Dickwella looks to push it out on the off side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Length again but Shah offers width this time, Dickwella punches it off the back foot but finds the man at point.
Pitched up around off, this is gently pushed towards mid off. Naseem Shah has overstepped and a no ball is called.
On  a good length and over middle, Dickwella hangs back and works it off the inner half of the blade towards square leg.
FOUR! Skillful from Niroshan Dickwella! Shorter delivery, slanted across the left-hander. Dickwella bends his back and uses the pace of the ball to ramp it into the third man fence for a boundary.
Fuller and around off, Dickwella plays inside the line of the ball.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Naseem Shah draws first blood! Shah serves it on a driving length and angles it well across the off stump. Niroshan Dickwella just can't help himself from playing at it and pays the price. Dickwella presses forward and tries to drive away from his body as the ball takes the outside edge and Mohammad Rizwan makes no mistake behind the sticks. Sri Lanka lose an early wicket and Shah is ecstatic.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Full and around off, pushed firmly towards mid on for a single.
Good length, on the pads and this is tucked away behind square for a single.
Pitches it up now, around off, this is defended off the front foot.
Back of a length and on the body, this is played off the back foot by Fernando past backward square leg for one.
Shorter and around off, Mendis leaves it alone.
Goes full and wide, Kusal Mendis makes an easy leave.
Around the top of off, this is blocked off the front foot towards mid on.
Around off, defended off the front foot.
A length ball on off, Oshada Fernando pushes it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! An attempted short ball, sits up at a comfortable height for the batter. Oshada Fernando swivel-pulls it into the backward square leg fence with ease.
FOUR! Length ball, around off and shaping away a touch, Oshada Fernando opens the face of the bat and drives it on the up, through point for back-to-back boundaries.
Naseem goes a bit wide of the crease and angles it into middle and off, Fernando gets behind the line to make a solid block.
FOUR! This is a poor delivery from Hasan Ali and it is put away easily. Short and wide, Kusal Mendis with a punch off the back foot and the ball races through covers for a boundary.
Good length, around the fifth stump line, left alone by Mendis.
Goes a bit fuller and outside off once again, Mendis just shoulders arms at it.
Ali angles it in full and on leg stump, trying to shape it away from there but Mendis stays watchful in defense.
Full and on off, punched away towards mid off.
Length again, angling down leg, Kusal Mendis looks to flick but gets it off the pads. Mohammad Rizwan does well to dive down to his left and get a glove on it.
This is slanted into middle and leg, Fernando pushes it out towards mid on.
A bumper now, over middle, Oshada Fernando gets on top of the bounce and plays a controlled pull shot down to deep square leg for a single.
Full and attacking the pads, Mendis nudges it out on the leg side.
Good shot for no run! Pitched up, around off and this is driven on the bounce to the man at extra cover.
This is a tad fuller and shaping in late from around off, Kusal Mendis watches it all the way through and makes the block.
FOUR! Glorious! This is a half-volley around off, Kusal Mendis creams it through extra cover for a boundary and even holds the pose.

OUT! LBW! Yasir Shah gets a wicket off his very first delivery of this innings. This is floated on middle, straightens after hiiting the deck, Oshada Fernando goes for the front-foot block but misses and gets hit on the pads right in front of the stumps. He is playing for the turn but there isn't any and this is what beats him. There is a huge shout for LBW and it is given. Oshada Fernando discusses with his partner Mendis and decides not to take the review and rightly so, this is plumb in front.
Howout: lbw b Yasir Shah

Commentary: Flighted on middle, turning away, Angelo Mathews pushes it of his back foot to mid on for a run. He gets off the mark straightaway.
Tossed up on middle, Kusal Mendis blocks it out.

EDGED BUT DROPPED! This is slower through the air on off, turning away sharply, Kusal Mendis tries to work it to the off side but gets a thin outside edge towards the first slip. Babar Azam there dives to his left but cannot grab it as the ball goes towards short fine leg off his hands. They cross.
Tossed up full on off, Angelo Mathews drives it to mid on.
Quicker and a bit short on middle, Angelo Mathews stays back and blocks it out. End of a very eventful over.
Back of a length and outside off, Kusal Mendis pushes it to covers, the fielder does well to stop it diving to his left. They cross.
On a length and on middle, Angelo Mathews knocks it down the pitch.
Bangs it short this time, on middle and leg, Angelo Mathews ducks under it.
Goes fuller and on middle, Angelo Mathews works it to mid on.
Full once again but outside off this time, Angelo Mathews drives it firmly but straight to mid off.
Fullish and on middle, Angelo Mathews tries to push to mid off but mistimes his shot towards mid on instead.
Floated on middle, Kusal Mendis leans on and blocks it towards silly point.
Tossed up on leg, turning away, Kusal Mendis once again is solid in his defense.
Shortish and on middle, Kusal Mendis slaps it of his back foot towards short mid-wicket.
Shorter in length again and outside off, Kusal Mendis pushes it off his back foot through covers for one.
On middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Shah bowls the flipper this time, it is almost in the blockhole and on middle, Angelo Mathews digs it out towards mid off.
Mohammad Nawaz starts his spell with a nicely tossed up delivery, on middle, Kamindu Mendis knocks it back to the bowler.
Floated full and on off, Kamindu Mendis gets to the pitch of it and guides it to point.
Flighted on off, Kusal Mendis eases it through covers for a single.
FOUR! SLAPPED! This is short and outside off, Angelo Mathews makes room and slaps it of his back foot through extra covers for a boundary. The lead goes past 200 now for Sri Lanka.
Tossed up full on middle, Angelo Mathews knocks it to the off side by opening the face of his bat.
On middle, blocked out.
Flighted on middle and off, turning away a bit, Kusal Mendis pushes it towards cover-point.
Tossed up full and outside off, Kusal Mendis strides forward and drives it through covers for one.
Shah tries the googly this time, but bowls it way down the leg side. Angelo Mathews lets it go and Mohammad Rizwan could not collect it properly. The batters run a bye.
Quicker and flatter this time on middle, Kusal Mendis defends it to the off side.
Flatter delivery and sliding in, Kusal Mendis stays back and knocks it with the inner half to short leg.
Floated full and on the leg stump, Kusal Mendis goes down and sweeps it through square leg for one.
Full and on off, tucked to mid on.

OUT! LBW! Mohammad Nawaz appeals and the umpire raises the dreaded finger. Kusal Mendis has a word with his partner and decides to walk back to the pavilion. It is looped up, full and on leg stump. Kusal Mendis gets down on one knee and tries to sweep it away but does not get bat on ball. The ball goes on to hit him on the pads. It looks plumb as it seems to be strightening rather than going on with the angle. Mohammad Nawaz makes a loud appeal and gets his first wicket of the innings.
Howout: lbw b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: Drifts in, around off. Dinesh Chandimal defends it to point.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
Floated and full, on middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal drives it to cover but not in the gap.
On the pads, tucked to square on the leg side. A maiden-wicket for Nawaz this time. Pakistan are making a strong statement with the ball here.
Fuller, on leg, Mathews flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Around off, blocked out solidly.
Almost through the defences. Flighted and full, on off. Dinesh Chandimal looks to block it out and does so with the inner half to the leg side.
On off, Chandimal presses forward and blocks it away.
It is slower through the air, around leg, turning away. Dinesh Chandimal keeps his eyes on the ball and blocks it solidly in the end.
On the pads, tucked to the leg side. A tidy over from Shah comes to an end.
Touch short, outside off. Angelo Mathews cuts it hard to sweeper cover for a single.
A dot now! It is darted on the pads, Dinesh Chandimal nudges it to square leg.
Slower one, full and on off. Chandimal gets it to mid on off the inner half.
Short ball, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal punches it to cover for a single.
Good running! Full, outside off. Mathews leans in and drives it to mid off. He scampers through for a quick single.
Fuller, on leg. Chandimal eases it back to the bowler.
Looped up, around middle and leg. Mathews looks to flik it away but misses.
Tossed up full and on off, Angelo Mathews gets a big stride forward and drives it to short extra covers.
Short and wide on off, Angelo Mathews hangs back and slaps it hard but cannot get past short covers. He is unhappy with himself as this was there to put away.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated full on leg, Angelo Mathews clears his front leg and looks to whip on the leg side but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Shah starts with a maiden after drinks.This is a classic leg spin delivery, tossed up, on middle, turning away, Angelo Mathews watches it well and blocks it out.
On middle and leg, defended back to the bowler.
Fuller, outside off. Chandimal taps it to point.
CLOSE! How has that missed the edge? It drifts in, pitches on off and spins away sharply. Dinesh Chandimal tries to block it away but does so inside the line. It zips past the outside edge.
On off, pushed to covers.
Floated and full, on off. This one stays low off the deck. Dinesh Chandimal goes back and does enough to push the ball away.
Tossed up, around middle. Chandimal pushes it to mid off. A maiden for Nawaz now.
On a nagging length and drifted onto middle, Mathews goes deep in his crease to keep it out.
Drifted down leg, Angelo Mathews tickles it away towards fine leg for an easy single.
Floated up, around leg stump, Dinesh Chandimal nudges it out in front of short leg.
'Catch it,' is the call from the keeper but its a bit too far away. This is sliding into the pads, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it past short leg and towards backward square leg for a couple of runs.
Around middle, blocked out by Chandimal.
Nicely tossed up, around middle, this is caressed towards extra cover.
This is angled in from around off, Mathews backs away and punches it towards cover.
Flighted, on off, Mathews leans forward to make the block.
Nice bit of loop outside off, encouraging the drive. Angelo Mathews drives it gently towards the cover region.
Drifted into middle, Mathews makes a watchful block.
Floated up on leg stump, Angelo Mathews flicks it to the left of the man at mid-wicket who does well to get a hand on it. The batters sneak in a run.
Full, on middle and leg, this is nudged away towards silly mid on.
FOUR! Gets it through! This is dragged down around the off pole, Angelo Mathews is quick to get onto the back foot and punches it through extra cover to find the fence.
Slower through the air and looped up a bit, around off, Mathews blocks off the front foot.
Nicely drifted onto middle and leg, Mathews blocks it out with soft hands.
Holds it back a touch and flights it on off, kept out by Mathews once again.
This is drifted onto the pads, Mathews defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Poor delivery from Yasir Shah and that's easy pickings for Angelo Mathews. This is short and on off, Mathews has enough time to rock back and uses his wrists to work it past the diving fielder at wide mid on for a boundary.
Quicker delivery, darted into middle, Chandimal solidly keeps it out on the off side.
Just held back a touch and flighted full on off, Chandimal eases it through covers and picks up a single.

SIX! Clean strike! Tossed up, on off, Angelo Mathews stands tall and just swings freely through the line to dispatch it a long way over the long off fence. Mathews getting a move on here with some aggressive intent.
Immediately pulls back the length and bowls it around off, Mathews can't get it through covers.
On middle and leg, blocked out by Mathews.
Drifts it nicely into leg stump, Mathews watches it well and turns it to mid-wicket.
Nauman starts off with a flatter delivery around off, Dinesh Chandimal plays it off the back foot and towards sweeper cover for a run.
On off, Mathews presses forward to defend.
Floated up, full and around off, Mathews keeps it out.
On the shorter side, around off. Angelo Mathews goes back and across to ease it through covers for a run.
A hint of flight, around off, Chandimal pushes it towards cover.
Just a tad short and outside off, this is cut away off the back foot but straight towards point.
Short and well outside off, Angelo Mathews stays back and cuts it through cover-point for one.
Floated full and on leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it away to short mid-wicket.
Flatter and around off, Dinesh Chandimal makes room and punches it through covers for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Angelo Mathews leans on and defends it onto the pitch.
Darts this on the leg stump, too full, Angelo Mathews knocks it back to the bowler.
Nawaz pulls his length back and bowls this around off, Angelo Mathews once again eases it towards long off for one. He looks in good touch.
TURN AND BOUNCE! This is floated on off, turning away sharply, Angelo Mathews goes for the block but the extra bounce surprises him and goes on to hit the top of his bat.
Tossed up on leg, Angelo Mathews knocks it towards short mid on with the inner half of his bat.
Flatter delivery on off, Angelo Mathews pushes it to cover-point.
FOUR! SMASHED! This is flighted on off, Angelo Mathews dances down the track and smashes it over mid off for another boundary.
Nice use of the feet by Mathews. This is short and around off, Angelo Mathews moves back and cuts it through covers for a single.
Pitches it up on off, Dinesh Chandimal taps it to point.
Agha Salman starts with a floater, full and on leg, Angelo Mathews tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Full again and on middle, Angelo Mathews uses his feet and drills it towards long on for a run.
This is flighted on middle, angling in, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it with the inner half past short leg. They cross.
Tossed up full on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it down the pitch.
Slightly shorter and on middle and leg, Angelo Mathews adjust his feet and pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Full and sliding on leg, Angelo Mathews clips it to mid-wicket again.
Floated on middle, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it to short leg.
Tossed up full onto the stumps, Dinesh Chandimal drives it to short covers.
Goes full again and on off, Dinesh Chandimal eases it towards long off for one.
Pushed quciker and on middle, this is blocked back to the bowler.
Tossed up again and on off, Angelo Mathews punches it to the left of the bowler and towards long off for another single.
Slower through the air on off, turning away a bit, Dinesh Chandimal gets on top of it and slaps it to long off for another run.
Darted on the pads, Chandimal flicks it to square leg for one.
On off, blocked out solidly.
It is full and down leg, Mathews flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Chandimal flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pakistan are ecstatic as they get their man with the help of the review. There is appeal for a catch! The umpire is not interested. Babar Azam is convinced by his bowler and takes the review. It is tossed up, around off, turning a touch off the deck. Angelo Mathews stays back and tries to block it away but does so inside the line. The ball seems to have bounced off the pads, as Babar Azam hops and grabs it at first slip. The UltraEdge though later confirms that there is a spike as the ball passes the blade. The umpire is forced to overturn his decision and Angelo Mathews trudges back to the pavilion shaking his head. Also, its a maiden Test wicket for Agha Salman.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Agha Salman

Commentary: Dimuth Karunaratne is off the mark straightaway. It is full and outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne drives it to covers for a single. The lead moves to 248 now.
Flatter, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it to point.
Slower through the air, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne comes down the track and works it to mid on for one.
Fuller, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it gently towards covers.
This is pitched up, outside off, with some extra bounce. Dinesh Chandimal tries to cut it away but gets beaten on the inside edge.
On off, blocked out.
On the pads, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
Full ball, on off. Chandimal drills it to long on for a single.
A full toss, on the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne misses out this time, as he flicks it straight to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Full and on off, driven to mid on for a single.
On off, defended out.
Full and on off. Dinesh Chandimal works it to long on for a single.
On the stumps. Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it back to the bowler watchfully.
This is sliding into the pads, Chandimal flicks it to mid on and rotates the strike.
This is on middle and leg, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it to square leg for one.
On off, pushed to cover for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne shuffles across and blocks it out on the front foot.
Flighted and full, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne shuffles across and works it back to the bowler off the toe-end.
This one spins in from outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne stays back and defends it out solidly. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3.
Agha Salman starts with a floater and down the leg, Dinesh Chandimal tickles it away towards fine leg for a brace.
Tossed up full and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it back to the bowler who makes a good stop moving to his right.
A bit short and on off, Dinesh Chandimal punches it off his back foot towards short covers.
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal looks to work it to the leg side but closes the face of his bat a bit early, the ball goes of the leading but wide of the bowler.
Darts this one down the leg again, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it wide of fine leg and picks up two.

Tossed up on middle, blocked out. It is called a no ball not for overstepping but there were three fielders behind square on the leg side which is against the rules. The short leg fielder's right foot is behind square when the ball is delivered and Babar Azam seems unhappy with the umpire's decision.
Full and onto the pads, Dinesh Chandimal works it to mid-wicket.
Naseem Shah starts with a short ball on off, Dimuth Karunaratne pulls it through square leg for one.
On a length and on off, Dinesh Chandimal stays back and punches it to short covers.
Brilliant yorker by Shah. This is in the blockhole and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal does well to dig it out to the off side.
He bangs in short ball from 'round the wicket and on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne ducks under it. Dimuth Karunaratne is struggling with his back clearly.
Another short ball but this time on off, Dimuth Karunaratne decides not to duck this time and hooks it towards deep backward square leg for one.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Naseem Shah gets his man and this could be a huge moment in the game. This is full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal tries to go for the big booming drive from his crease and without any footwork. The ball takes a thin outside edge and goes towards the keeper Mohammad Rizwan who makes no mistake and takes a simple catch moving to his right. Sri Lanka lead by 264 runs.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Tossed up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it to the off side.
Flighted around middle, Dimuth Karunaratne is solid in his defense.
Floated on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes this back to the bowler.
Slower through the air and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne mistimes his drive to short mid off.
Shortish and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne cuts it from his back foot towards point where the fielder does well to stop the ball diving to his right.
On off, knocked back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, angling in, Dhananjaya de Silva tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good length and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva opens the face of his bat and guides it to point.

FOUR! Dhananjaya de Silva gets off the mark with a boundary. Shah tries to bowl a bouncer but it is on comfortable length for the batter, de Silva gets on top of it and pulls it away in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
On a length and around off, Dhananjaya de Silva leans on and knocks it to the off side.
Good length and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva tries to guide it towards the third man for one but hits it straight to point.
Fullish delivery on off, Dhananjaya de Silva defends it down the pitch.
BEATEN! Salman gives this a bit of air and lands it on off, turning away slightly, Dimuth Karunaratne leans on to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Flatter delivery on off, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it to covers.
Short and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne cuts it from his back foot to point.
Short again and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne this time manages to punch it through cover-point for one.
Tossed up full and on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva strides forward and defends it on the front foot.
Salman bowls this short again and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva makes room and cuts it past point for one.
This is on a length and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and punches it well towards short covers. Yasir Shah does well to stop it diving to his left. He certainly saved a boundary there.
Fullish delivery and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva drives it towards mid off.
Pulls his length back a bit and this is around off, Dhananjaya de Silva moves towards the ball and knocks it to point.
Outside off, left alone.

Just short! This is a good-length delivery and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes to block it but gets a thick outside edge and the ball falls just short of the second slip fielder. Naseem Shah is bowling really well here.
Full and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva drives it to mid off.
Shorter in length and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne cuts it past point for one.
Tossed up full and on middle and leg, Dhananjaya de Silva wrists it towards long on and picks up a single.

Darted full on middle, angling in, Dimuth Karunaratne uses his feet to work it to the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a stiffled appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested.
On off, kept out.
Quicker and flatter around off, Dimuth Karunaratne offers no shot at it.

FOUR BYES! This is fired in way down the leg side, Dimuth Karunaratne misses his flick and the ball goes past the keeper as well, it races away towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. Pakistan cannot afford to gift runs like this.
This is looped up, outside off, turning away. Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and cuts it straight to the fielder at point.
Floated and full, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it out.
Touch short, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva goes back and fends it out.

FOUR! Neatly played by Dhananjaya de Silva. It is tossed up, outside off, spinning away. Dhananjaya de Silva waits for it, reaches out and guides it down to third man. Fawad Alam gives it a chase, puts in a dive and tries to keep the ball in play but touches the cushion in the process. A valiant effort nonetheless.
On off, blocked out.

FOUR! Smashed! Dhananjaya de Silva gets the second boundary of the over. The lead moves to 284. It is short and on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva pulls it through the gap at mid-wicket and finds the boundary.
Slower through the air, on the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Dhananjaya de Silva is on a roll here. It is short, wide outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva goes back and cuts it through covers for a boundary. The stand moves to 25.

FOUR BYES! Babar Azam fires it down the leg side. Dhananjaya de Silva misses to tuck it away. Mohammad Rizwan moves to his left but the ball evades him. It races away to the fine leg fence. The umpire signals byes.
Flatter, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva tries to cut it away but inside-edges in on the deck.
Floated and full, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it to covers.

Length ball, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva punches it through covers. The batters push hard for the first one. Dhananjaya de Silva wanted the second run but Dimuth Karunaratne is clearly struggling with his back and denies for the second run.
