This is angled into middle from around the stumps, kept out by Nawaz.

A appeal for stumping! This could be close. Tossed up, outside off. It grips and turns away. Nawaz tries to defend inside the line but misses. Niroshan Dickwella collects and clips the bails quickly. The umpire takes it upstairs to confirm. The UltraEdge show no bat is involved. The side-on angled shows that Nawaz had his back foot grounded. The final decision is NOT OUT.
Nice bit of drift into the off stump, Nawaz watchfully keeps it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! This is poor cricket from Mohammad Nawaz, he just didn't have the temperament to defend and pays the price. This is floated up very full and around middle, turning away a touch. Nawaz tries to go for the big shot, against the turn and ends up slicing it high. The ball loops up around the cover region where Dinesh Chandimal takes a simple catch. The deadly duo of Jayasuriya and Mendis doing the job here for Sri Lanka who are now three wickets away from victory.
Howout: c Dinesh Chandimal b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Looped up, full and on off, turning in, Hasan Ali keeps it out towards short leg.
Tossed up, around off, Ali strides forward to make the block. A wicket maiden them for Ramesh Mendis!
FOUR! Full and on middle and leg, Yasir Shah decides to have a crack at it and heaves it in front of mid-wicket and collects a boundary.
On a nagging length, on off and turning away, Shah prods forward to defend.
FOUR! Just a bit too full and too straight from Jayasuriya. This is on leg stump, Yasir Shah drives it through wide mid on and picks up yet another boundary.
FOUR! A third boundary in the over and Yasir Shah enjoying his stay at the crease for now. Tossed up, full and on off, Shah pummels it uppishly and through mid on for a boundary.
Much better from Jayasuriya. Flighted, close to the off pole and turning away sharply. Yasir Shah plays inside the line of the ball.
Tosses it up again, drawing the batter forward. This is outside off, Shah drives it gently towards extra cover.
A tad shorter and on the pads, Hasan Ali works it 'round the corner for a single.

FOUR! That is a shot of real confidence and it looks like Yasir Shah wants to give a bit of stick back to the bowlers. Tossed up, around middle, Shah dances down the track and lofts it one-bounce into the mid-wicket fence.
FOUR! Yasir Shah dealing in just boundaries at the moment. On a length and around middle, Shah gets a big stride forward and sweeps it hard, through mid-wicket for yet another boundary.
Fuller and around off, Shah makes the block.
Quicker and flatter, turning it in from outside off. Yasir Shah watchfully keeps it out.
Around off again, Shah looks to drive but gets it off the inside edge and towards backward square leg for a single.
On the bounce! Nice bit of drift into middle and leg, Yasir Shah pushes at it with soft hands and the ball lands just in front of the man at silly point.
FOUR! Deft touch! Full and floated on the pads, Shah with a fine tickle this time and the ball runs away into the fine leg fence.
A bit of drift again into the right-hander, Shah negates it well.
Sliding into the pads, Shah keeps it out.
Drifted onto the pads, trying to turn it away from there. Yasir Shah nudges it off the inside edge and though leg slip for a couple of runs.
Very full and on middle, driven towards mid off.
On off, blocked out.
Fuller, around off, defended out.
FOUR! Boundaries are flowing for Pakistan. It is full, going down leg. Ali tickles it fine. It races away to the fine leg boundary.
Fuller, on middle, defended out solidly.
On off, defended on the front foot.
SIX! BANG! It is tossed up, full and outside off. Ali lofts it overs the bowler's head for a biggie.
Around middle, Shah gets a big stride forward to defend.
A bit flatter and around off, Shah keeps it out towards silly point.
Fuller, on the pads, clipped to short leg.
Four dots on the trot! Fuller, outside off. Shah drives it to mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! Prabath Jayasuriya picks up his fifth wicket of the innings. He has been consistent for the hosts throughout this series. Yasir Shah's cameo comes to an end. It is tossed up, around middle and leg, drifting in. Shah tries to flick it away but is a tad early into his shot. It takes the leading edge and goes to gully. Kusal Mendis takes a sitter. Sri Lanka now need two more wickets to win the game.
Howout: c Kusal Mendis b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Fuller, on off, Ali blocks it back to the bowler.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Another man bites the dust for Pakistan. Mendis gets his third wicket now. It is full and on off. Ali looks to sweep it away but does not connect. It hits him on the pads, might've got some arm on it as well, as he goes through with the shot. It goes onto disturb the bails. Sri Lanka need just a wicket now.
Howout: b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Flighted on middle, turning in, Naseem Shah pads it away. It looks close and there is an appeal for LBW but turned down.
BEATEN! This floated around off, Naseem Shah goes for the block but is beaten on the outside edge.
Shah living on the edge here. This is tossed up on middle, Naseem Shah goes for the big shot but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
SIX! Shah is trying to attack. This is flighted and full on off, Naseem Shah makes room and smokes it over extra covers for a biggie.
Pushed through quicker onto the pads, Shah tickles it to fine leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Floated and full, on fourth stump. Shah looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On off, defended out.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Shah blocks it out watchfully.
SIX! BANG! Fuller, on off. Shah offers full face of the bat and tonks it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Fuller, outside off, turns away a touch. Shah gets it to point off the outer half.
Floated full and on middle, Nauman Ali knocks it to silly point.
Tossed up full and on middle, Nauman Ali pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish and outside off, Ali stays back and punches it to silly point.
Flighted on middle, turning away, Ali blocks it with his outer half to the off side.
Flighted delivery and on middle, angling in, Ali goes for defense but inside edges it past short leg.
Maiden over by Mendis. This is tossed up around off, Ali keeps it out.
Tossed up, on the stumps. Shah defends it out.
This one comes in with the arm, full and on middle, blocked out solidly.
Darted on the pads, Shah goes back and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller, down leg. Shah clips it to square leg for a single.
Looped up, outside off, turns in a touch. Ali stays back and tries to punch it away but misses. It goes to fine leg after hitting the pads.
Full and off, pushed to covers.
Flighted on off, turning in, Shah blocks it onto the pitch.
Tossed up on middle, Shah comes down the track to loft it over mid-wicket but gets an inside edge and it goes towards short leg.
Floated on off, turning in sharply, Shah is caught in his crease but manages to defend it well.
FOUR! A gift from Mendis. This is a full toss and on off, Shah smashes it through extra covers for a boundary.
Full again on off, turning in. Shah knocks it to the off side.

OUT! TAKEN! Mendis gets the last man and the Sri Lankans are delighted and there are celebratory scenes all over the ground. This is floated and on off, turning in, Naseem Shah tries to go for the big shot across the line again but this time mistimes his shot. The ball goes high in the air towards Dunith Wellalage who is stationed at deep mid-wicket judges it well and pouches it safely. Sri Lanka win the game by 246 runs.
Howout: c Dunith Wellalage b Ramesh Mendis
